	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816364">
		<article id="div-comment-816364" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Era									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Oh, this is going on the &#8216;we&#8217;re having this tonight&#8217; list immediately! Makes me want to pair it with more tex mex flavours, like guacamole. Am loving this recipe at the moment: <a href="http://kitchenfeasts.com/2015/02/25/guacamole/" rel="nofollow ugc">http://kitchenfeasts.com/2015/02/25/guacamole/</a></p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T12:28:16-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816364">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:28 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816364#respond" data-commentid="816364" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816364" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Era" aria-label="Reply to Era">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816364 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816365">
		<article id="div-comment-816365" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Jill									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I love everything chickpea and your site has been a treasure chest of ideas for them. Cannot stop eating that lemon tahini dressing from the butternut squash and chickpea recipe on all sorts of things. Thrilled to try this one too. Simple, hearty meals make the world go round.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T12:33:00-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816365">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:33 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816365#respond" data-commentid="816365" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816365" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jill" aria-label="Reply to Jill">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816365 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816366">
		<article id="div-comment-816366" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Alison Hannah									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Looks delish, will be sure to make it this evening but with canned chickpeas. Love the website as always!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T12:33:10-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816366">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:33 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816366#respond" data-commentid="816366" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816366" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Alison Hannah" aria-label="Reply to Alison Hannah">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816366 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816367">
		<article id="div-comment-816367" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Lauren									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>What vegetable broth do you use. I tried the better than bouillon vegetable paste because I loved the chicken when I still ate meat, but it was awful.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T12:35:49-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816367">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:35 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816367#respond" data-commentid="816367" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816367" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lauren" aria-label="Reply to Lauren">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816367 -->
	 </li>
	<ol class="children">
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-debsk bypostauthor even depth-2" id="comment-816370">
		<article id="div-comment-816370" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://smittenkitchen.com">deb</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Lauren &#8212; This time I used Pacific organic, low sodium. It was pretty good in here. I agree some are terrible; I still have nightmares about the one that was basically thin pureed carrots. If you just want to use water, I think that can still work, but you might want to bump up the seasonings.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T12:37:34-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816370">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:37 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816370#respond" data-commentid="816370" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816370" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to deb" aria-label="Reply to deb">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816370 -->
	 </li>
	<ol class="children">
	<li class="comment odd alt depth-3" id="comment-1360627">
