	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816389">
		<article id="div-comment-816389" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://thejameskitchen.wordpress.com">Nicole @ thejameskitchen</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Oooooh, lovely! Not that I had planned a different chickpea dish today (&amp;stuffed mushrooms) but this looks like I might change the menu. Chickpeas &amp; a spiced yoghurt are welcome in our house any time. Nicole</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T13:30:47-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816389">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:30 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816389#respond" data-commentid="816389" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816389" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Nicole @ thejameskitchen" aria-label="Reply to Nicole @ thejameskitchen">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816389 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816390">
		<article id="div-comment-816390" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Nicole R.									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>You are a GENIUS. </p>
<p>Now, since you already answered the vegan and gluten-free questions so people can&#8217;t get you with those&#8230;I am envisioning this in a slow cooker. Do you think I would need to reduce the liquid?</p>
<p>It&#8217;s tax season for me, so the idea of getting home (around 9:30 pm&#8230;) and eating this in the time it takes to make the salsa and toast some pita is MAGICAL.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T13:32:09-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816390">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:32 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816390#respond" data-commentid="816390" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816390" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Nicole R." aria-label="Reply to Nicole R.">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816390 -->
	 </li>
	<ol class="children">
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-debsk bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-816394">
		<article id="div-comment-816394" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://smittenkitchen.com">deb</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Nicole &#8212; Since you&#8217;re not going to be home, it might be safer to use more liquid because it&#8217;s better to have too much and drain them off a little with a slotted spoon as you scoop then than to have them burning in there while you&#8217;re away, leaving you with no dinner. And thank you. (P.S. I hate tax season too, but for opposite reasons!)</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T13:39:34-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816394">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:39 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816394#respond" data-commentid="816394" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816394" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to deb" aria-label="Reply to deb">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816394 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816391">
		<article id="div-comment-816391" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Lindsay									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>OMG, must make this tonight!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T13:33:30-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816391">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:33 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816391#respond" data-commentid="816391" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816391" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lindsay" aria-label="Reply to Lindsay">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816391 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816392">
		<article id="div-comment-816392" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.lovefromberlin.net/">Rae</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This recipe looks so lovely &#8211; really perfect for a Saturday afternoon. I am bookmarking this one and will make it very soon! Thanks for the great recipe. You can never go wrong with chickpeas!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T13:34:41-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816392">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:34 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816392#respond" data-commentid="816392" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816392" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Rae" aria-label="Reply to Rae">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816392 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816393">
		<article id="div-comment-816393" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.recipefiction.com">Melinda @ RecipeFiction</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Okay this looks amazing! And almost all the ingredients are on hand in my kitchen right now. For want of a cucumber the salad will not be lost! I too have a nut allergy but I don&#8217;t think I&#8217;d be missing a thing without the pine nuts (except a stab of the epipen) perhaps some oven crisped greens instead for one more layer of crunch.Yay nachos!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T13:39:06-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816393">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:39 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816393#respond" data-commentid="816393" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816393" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Melinda @ RecipeFiction" aria-label="Reply to Melinda @ RecipeFiction">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816393 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816395">
		<article id="div-comment-816395" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											tamara									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>this looks AMAZING and is reminiscent of a super delicious Palestinian dish called fattet hummus! see link below. bravo, deb! you must have been a middle eastern person in a past life! </p>
<p><a href="http://www.kitchenofpalestine.com/fattet-hummus/" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.kitchenofpalestine.com/fattet-hummus/</a><br />
(the dish is not always as wet as it is in this recipe, and is often more generously garnished, like yours!)</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T13:41:38-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816395">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:41 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816395#respond" data-commentid="816395" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816395" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to tamara" aria-label="Reply to tamara">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816395 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816396">
