	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816402">
		<article id="div-comment-816402" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://apinchofthis.nyc">Tory</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>what a good idea. i can definitely see adding some ground lamb too, if you really need to add meat.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T14:52:47-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816402">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">2:52 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816402#respond" data-commentid="816402" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816402" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Tory" aria-label="Reply to Tory">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816402 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816403">
		<article id="div-comment-816403" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Randy									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>When is your next cook book coming out???  Please??  I love your recipes.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T15:01:35-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816403">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">3:01 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816403#respond" data-commentid="816403" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816403" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Randy" aria-label="Reply to Randy">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816403 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816404">
		<article id="div-comment-816404" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											La									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Middle Easterner chiming in here &#8211; totally made me think of hummus fattah! Mexican and Middle Eastern food have a lot more in common than you would think: lots of cilantro, cumin, tomato/onion/cucumber salads, citrus, grilled meats, chiles&#8230; you can thank the Moors that settled in Mexico for the blending of the cultures.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T15:09:09-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816404">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">3:09 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816404#respond" data-commentid="816404" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816404" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to La" aria-label="Reply to La">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816404 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816405">
		<article id="div-comment-816405" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Emily									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>And to think &#8211; I was just trying to dream up a recipe that would use up the leftover (and slowly turning) tomatoes, onions, and pita in the fridge. This is GENIUS. I might have to change up some of the ingredients a bit here and there, sub some overdue mushrooms, sauteed, for the pine nuts, maybe a squeeze of lime to whittle away my store from a ill planned sale purchase (or create some middle eastern inspired margaritas to keep with the theme) but the bulk will be the same and I am so so excited to feed my addiction to both tex mex and middle eastern food. Thanks Deb, yet again, for the great recipe!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T15:20:41-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816405">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">3:20 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816405#respond" data-commentid="816405" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816405" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Emily" aria-label="Reply to Emily">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816405 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816406">
		<article id="div-comment-816406" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Rachel									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Looks great! Mercedes of Desert Candy wrote about something similar a few days ago: <a href="http://desertcandy.blogspot.ca/2015/03/nile-nachos.html" rel="nofollow ugc">http://desertcandy.blogspot.ca/2015/03/nile-nachos.html</a></p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T15:51:13-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816406">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">3:51 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816406#respond" data-commentid="816406" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816406" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Rachel" aria-label="Reply to Rachel">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816406 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816407">
		<article id="div-comment-816407" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Danielle									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Man, I am loving your vegetarian meals lately! So fresh and full of flavour! For me they feel like a good transition from winter to summer as there is the warming legumes with the freshness of the veg. I&#8217;ll be making this recipe ASAP. Tonight I am making your red bean and green grain taco bowl. Very excited for it.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T16:00:45-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816407">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">4:00 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816407#respond" data-commentid="816407" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816407" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Danielle" aria-label="Reply to Danielle">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816407 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816408">
		<article id="div-comment-816408" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Kelly									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>We&#8217;re on the same page! I made chickpeas last night too! Unfortunately now I&#8217;m out of them :( My standby for &#8220;middle eastern-ish&#8221; chickpeas are onion, garlic, a bunch of Harissa paste, veggie broth, lemon and parsley (with flatbread if I have it). Can&#8217;t wait to add this to the chickpea repitoire!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
