	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816422">
		<article id="div-comment-816422" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											JP									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Cook&#8217;s Illustrated suggests brining beans (salt in the soaking water) to really make them cook through and be tender.  I wonder if this would work with chick peas too?  I can attest that it does wonders with pinto and navy beans.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T19:18:01-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816422">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:18 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816422#respond" data-commentid="816422" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816422" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to JP" aria-label="Reply to JP">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816422 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816423">
		<article id="div-comment-816423" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://flashshoe.blogspot.com">Alina</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>&#8220;Middle Eastern nachos.&#8221; Brilliant! I want to eat this now.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T19:39:15-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816423">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:39 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816423#respond" data-commentid="816423" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816423" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Alina" aria-label="Reply to Alina">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

