	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816425">
		<article id="div-comment-816425" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://chicdreamjar.blogspot.com/">Jackie</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I see that you&#8217;ve used Rancho Gordo and I love that company! I couldn&#8217;t agree more that summer couldn&#8217;t come any faster! Currently surviving on cellared vegetables&#8230;</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T20:29:29-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816425">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:29 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816425#respond" data-commentid="816425" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816425" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jackie" aria-label="Reply to Jackie">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816425 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816426">
		<article id="div-comment-816426" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Sarah									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This puts me in mind of the infamous chickpea dish at Melbourne&#8217;s Moroccan Soup Bar, with toasted almonds rather than pine nuts (highly recommend). Just googling &#8216;moroccan soup bar chickpea dish&#8217; gives you an idea of how beloved it is &#8211; many versions, but somehow mine never are quite like the original. But oh my, I&#8217;m trying this one this week.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T20:39:28-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816426">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:39 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816426#respond" data-commentid="816426" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816426" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Sarah" aria-label="Reply to Sarah">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816426 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816427">
		<article id="div-comment-816427" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Lynn									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>so do you do that thing where you squeeze the skin off the chickpeas like in the smoothest humus ever?</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T21:13:40-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816427">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:13 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816427#respond" data-commentid="816427" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816427" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lynn" aria-label="Reply to Lynn">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816427 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816428">
		<article id="div-comment-816428" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://pineapplespolkadots.blogspot.com">Elizabeth @ Pineapples and Polka Dots</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Yum!  This looks like such a fun and flavorful lunch, appetizer, or party dish!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T21:16:36-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816428">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:16 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816428#respond" data-commentid="816428" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816428" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Elizabeth @ Pineapples and Polka Dots" aria-label="Reply to Elizabeth @ Pineapples and Polka Dots">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816428 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816429">
		<article id="div-comment-816429" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.gatheranddine.com">emily | Gather &amp; Dine</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>So much to love about this!  Fun, festive, and healthy.  :)  Going on my list of meals for next week!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T21:17:42-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816429">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:17 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816429#respond" data-commentid="816429" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816429" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to emily | Gather &amp; Dine" aria-label="Reply to emily | Gather &amp; Dine">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816429 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816430">
		<article id="div-comment-816430" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Jenny									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>FYI in case you want to add a suggestion for your vegan friends: This lemon tahini sauce from (who else?) Yotam Ottolenghi totally rocks my world. First published in the guardian and then Jerusalem: <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2011/dec/16/roasted-squash-stuffed-quince-recipes" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2011/dec/16/roasted-squash-stuffed-quince-recipes</a> . He gets the proportions JUST RIGHT, as always.<br />
I&#8217;m in my early second trimester now, and this meal is hitting all my craving buttons!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T21:51:01-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816430">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:51 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816430#respond" data-commentid="816430" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816430" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jenny" aria-label="Reply to Jenny">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816430 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816431">
		<article id="div-comment-816431" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.chefdehome.com/">Savita @ ChefDeHome</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Beth, I cannot agree more! a dinner of these Mediterranean-style nachos can sure impress hungry (even not-so-hungry) souls! I won&#8217;t mind eating a few for lunch too! You won&#8217;t believe, we have similar bread in North India called Kulcha, and we eat it loaded just like these pitas but with Indian spices, tomatoes, cucumber, and masala chickpeas. Now, I&#8217;m craving for both! looks like have to try soon!!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T23:11:11-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816431">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:11 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816431#respond" data-commentid="816431" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816431" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Savita @ ChefDeHome" aria-label="Reply to Savita @ ChefDeHome">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816431 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816432">
		<article id="div-comment-816432" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.chefdehome.com/">Savita @ ChefDeHome</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>ooops! Deb, I called you &#8220;Beth&#8221; in excitement of these nachos you posted. :) Now you know for sure, how much I liked these! lol!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T23:13:13-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816432">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:13 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816432#respond" data-commentid="816432" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816432" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Savita @ ChefDeHome" aria-label="Reply to Savita @ ChefDeHome">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816432 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816433">
		<article id="div-comment-816433" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Haley									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Wow, this looks great, in large part because it reminds me of one of my favourite snacks, samosa chaat. Ever had it? It&#8217;s hot, crispy, potato and spice-filled samosa chopped up a bit on a plate, then drowned in saucy chickpeas, yogurt, tamarind sauce, sometimes fresh vegetables, and chaat spice. I love it! I seldom make it myself though, because I can get it for just 3$ at the friendly Indian sweet shop just up the street from me. I came to your site today to make your yellow dal (probably for the 20th time!), which I often make with white beans!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T23:26:33-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816433">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:26 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816433#respond" data-commentid="816433" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816433" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Haley" aria-label="Reply to Haley">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816433 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816434">
		<article id="div-comment-816434" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://imaginariyum.com">Sarah | The ImaginariYUM</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>OK, I dove right in and made it for dinner tonight. Used canned chickpeas since I didn&#8217;t even have time for the quick brining method, accidentally bought pita chips because I misread &#8220;for&#8221; as &#8220;or,&#8221; and totally forgot the pine nuts, but no worries &#8212; it was AMAZING. Might be the best non-pasta/gnocchi/risotto vegetarian dish I&#8217;ve ever made. The spices of the onions and chickpeas were just wonderful with the earthiness of the tahini yogurt sauce and brightness of the lemonized tomato-cucumber salad, and I loved the way the wetter ingredients sort of began to soften the pita chips beneath while still yielding a hearty crunch. The textures of everything together were just divine. So THANK YOU. I can&#8217;t wait for dinner again tomorrow.</p>
<p>One quick question: any thoughts on reheating the chickpeas for leftovers? Should I throw them back on the stove (there&#8217;s actually a decent amount of liquid left &#8212; I think I used closer to 2 cups) or straight into the microwave?</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-24T23:51:53-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816434">
						<span class="date">March 24, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:51 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816434#respond" data-commentid="816434" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816434" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Sarah | The ImaginariYUM" aria-label="Reply to Sarah | The ImaginariYUM">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816434 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816435">
		<article id="div-comment-816435" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://nettiescloset.com">Nettie</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I love chickpeas but I have never tried cooking them. I&#8217;m always trying to find a good chickpea recipe and go from there. This looks so delicious and I am actually inspired to cook some this weekend.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-25T00:13:20-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816435">
						<span class="date">March 25, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:13 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816435#respond" data-commentid="816435" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816435" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Nettie" aria-label="Reply to Nettie">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816435 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816436">
		<article id="div-comment-816436" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
