						<span class="date">March 25, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:13 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816459#respond" data-commentid="816459" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816459" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to sarah | little house pantry" aria-label="Reply to sarah | little house pantry">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816459 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816460">
		<article id="div-comment-816460" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Sonia									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Oh my!! This kind of sounds like a popular Indian Street food called Papri Chaat (<a href="http://www.vegrecipesofindia.com/papdi-chaat-delhi-papdi-chaat-recipe/" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.vegrecipesofindia.com/papdi-chaat-delhi-papdi-chaat-recipe/</a>)  which has crisp chips, chickpeas, yogurt, tamarind and mint chutneys..there are variations that add tomatoes and onions. Must try your version..<br />
Thanks!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-25T13:05:13-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816460">
						<span class="date">March 25, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:05 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
