					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816465#respond" data-commentid="816465" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816465" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Emily G" aria-label="Reply to Emily G">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816465 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816466">
		<article id="div-comment-816466" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.kdrose.com">Katie</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Had this for dinner last night and again for lunch today &#8211; so, so so good!  It&#8217;s borderline perfect food. :)  I completely forgot the homemade pita chips when I was packing my lunch this morning, so I had to use Sun Chips (the only thing remotely close to pita chips for sale in my building&#8217;s cafeteria) and it was also delicious.  I imagine you could just eat all the ingredients as a stew in that case and still die happy ;).</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-25T16:56:08-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816466">
						<span class="date">March 25, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">4:56 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816466#respond" data-commentid="816466" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816466" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Katie" aria-label="Reply to Katie">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816466 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816467">
		<article id="div-comment-816467" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Florence									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This was delicious, thank you! My husband made it this evening, with seeded tortillas (toasted in the oven) instead of pita. Thank you. I wonder if there&#8217;s a way to separate out the comments from people who haven&#8217;t made your recipes yet from those who have? It would make scanning through for ideas, questions and answers easier given how many fans you have!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-25T17:02:08-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816467">
						<span class="date">March 25, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">5:02 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816467#respond" data-commentid="816467" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816467" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Florence" aria-label="Reply to Florence">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816467 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816468">
		<article id="div-comment-816468" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.saltsugarandi.com">Dani Elis</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>You know what I have no problem with your mexican cravings&#8230; I have them too but mine are not from a bun in the oven mine are purely from the lack of mexican foods and ingredients available to me. This middle eastern dish looks delicious! can&#8217;t wait to give it a go :)</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-25T18:04:08-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816468">
						<span class="date">March 25, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">6:04 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816468#respond" data-commentid="816468" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816468" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Dani Elis" aria-label="Reply to Dani Elis">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816468 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816469">
		<article id="div-comment-816469" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Katy									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>What does baking the beans do that a slow simmer on the stove top wouldn&#8217;t accomplish? I don&#8217;t have any cookware that is safe for both the stovetop and the oven (I know, I should really get on that) and am wondering if I could just simmer it on the stove top.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-25T18:36:09-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816469">
						<span class="date">March 25, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">6:36 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816469#respond" data-commentid="816469" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816469" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Katy" aria-label="Reply to Katy">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816469 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816470">
		<article id="div-comment-816470" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.benevolent.net">Samantha B</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I just made this today and it was WONDERFUL! Thank you!</p>
<p>I did have a lot of liquid left over in my chickpeas. I had them soaking for about 24 hours. Perhaps 4 cups of broth was too much?</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-25T19:42:16-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816470">
						<span class="date">March 25, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:42 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816470#respond" data-commentid="816470" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816470" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Samantha B" aria-label="Reply to Samantha B">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816470 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816471">
		<article id="div-comment-816471" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Bettina									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I&#8217;ve been following this blog for a while and have already tried a recipe or two. The Middle Eastern Tex Mex is one of the best chickpea recipes we have ever eaten! DELICIOUS!! Will definitely become one of our favorite recipes! Thanks for blogging these great meals!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-25T20:13:50-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816471">
						<span class="date">March 25, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:13 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816471#respond" data-commentid="816471" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816471" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Bettina" aria-label="Reply to Bettina">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816471 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816472">
