	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816478">
		<article id="div-comment-816478" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Janice									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Good tip on patting the chickpeas dry before roasting, I could not get mine crispy when I tried.  Now I know why!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-26T08:35:25-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816478">
						<span class="date">March 26, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:35 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816478#respond" data-commentid="816478" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816478" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Janice" aria-label="Reply to Janice">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816478 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816479">
		<article id="div-comment-816479" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Janice									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Oh, I also wanted to ask, I spend a whole lot of time pulling the skins off each and every chickpea, is that necessary?  Am I the only one?</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-26T08:37:24-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816479">
						<span class="date">March 26, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:37 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816479#respond" data-commentid="816479" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816479" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Janice" aria-label="Reply to Janice">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816479 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816480">
		<article id="div-comment-816480" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Bess									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>We made this last night with canned chickpeas &#8211; delicious! We added roasted eggplant and feta. My four year old was crazy for it, and I ate so much that my pregnant belly still feels stretched this morning. Very quick too! And endlessly adaptable.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-26T08:53:53-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816480">
						<span class="date">March 26, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:53 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816480#respond" data-commentid="816480" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816480" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Bess" aria-label="Reply to Bess">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816480 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816481">
		<article id="div-comment-816481" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Lesley									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This was so delicious! Thank you! Came home very late yesterday evening to discover I only had one can of chickpeas and one can of cannellini beans, but I had to make this after seeing the photos. So good that I put the package of dried chickpeas I have in to soak overnight to make it again this weekend. I did have some chicken that needed to be grilled, so I marinated it in buttermilk, garlic, and ras el hanout. It was really nice pulled and tossed in with the beans, but definitely not necessary. I imagine this will be in very regular rotation at our house!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-26T09:02:31-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816481">
						<span class="date">March 26, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:02 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816481#respond" data-commentid="816481" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816481" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lesley" aria-label="Reply to Lesley">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816481 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816482">
		<article id="div-comment-816482" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.benevolent.net">Samantha B</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>We have a ton of the tahini-yogurt sauce left over.  Do you have any suggestions on what else can be done with it?  Perhaps marinating or as a dressing on a salad?</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-26T10:07:37-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816482">
						<span class="date">March 26, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">10:07 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816482#respond" data-commentid="816482" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816482" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Samantha B" aria-label="Reply to Samantha B">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816482 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816483">
		<article id="div-comment-816483" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.beardogco.com/theroadhome">Liz</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I cooked garbanzos (Rancho Gordo!) stove top this morning&#8230;saw this post and although I intended to cool them for hummus and freeze some, saved a few warm and mashed them.  I often have the &#8220;relish&#8221; which I eat as a salad so I mashed the beans on homemade toasted crusty bread, topped with relish, yogurt, lemon and parsley and called it a delicious breakfast!  I guess I&#8217;ll call it middle eastern beans on toast :)!</p>
<p>I didn&#8217;t take time yet to read all comments, but in case no one has said&#8230;beans freeze VERY well.  It is just me, but I usually make a big pot of whatever kind, cook them and freeze single use portions.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-26T10:46:07-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816483">
						<span class="date">March 26, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">10:46 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816483#respond" data-commentid="816483" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816483" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Liz" aria-label="Reply to Liz">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816483 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816484">
		<article id="div-comment-816484" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Mary B.									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I had some dried garbanzo beans that had been in the pantry for who knows how long, so I didn&#8217;t hold out too much hope for this, but it was so delicious. I got a call while the onions were in the pan so they got brown, which made them even more flavorful. Simple comfort food. Thanks Deb.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-26T11:33:37-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816484">
						<span class="date">March 26, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:33 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816484#respond" data-commentid="816484" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816484" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Mary B." aria-label="Reply to Mary B.">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816484 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816485">
		<article id="div-comment-816485" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Mary									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>how many cups of dry chickpeas is in one pound? I plan to cook the chickpeas in my pressure cooker first. Do you think that will work ok?</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-26T12:31:07-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816485">
						<span class="date">March 26, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:31 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816485#respond" data-commentid="816485" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816485" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Mary" aria-label="Reply to Mary">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816485 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-debsk bypostauthor even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816486">
		<article id="div-comment-816486" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://smittenkitchen.com">deb</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Stephanie, Katy &#8212; The reason for baking them is that I find it to be a gentler way to cook them, and cook them evenly. That said, I do think this would work on the stove, just keep it barely simmering and use the heaviest pot you have. It&#8217;s also totally fine to make this without a stove-to-oven pot. Just saut&#233; everything in a  skillet and transfer it to a casserole dish; you can wrap it in foil if you don&#8217;t have a lid. </p>
<p>Florence &#8212; Yes, there will be, or at least some threading of comments if The Slowest Redesign Ever for this site (1 year and counting!) is ever finished. :)</p>
<p>Shireen &#8212; My husband likes Tapatio. I like Rancho Gordo&#8217;s Mild Sauce for Hot People. :)</p>
<p>Sara &#8212; I think a lot could be made ahead. Definitely the beans, up to a couple days. They might need a little extra broth or water when reheated because they&#8217;ll likely keep &#8220;drinking&#8221; as they rest. The pita chips I made kept well for a few days, as did the toasted pine nuts. The sauce keeps in the fridge. The salad ingredients could be chopped and just dressed before eating. You can dress it sooner, but soften things more. Hope that helps. </p>
<p>Mary &#8212; I had 2 1/2 cups. I think this would work great in a pressure cooker. </p>
<p>Samanatha B &#8212; I originally used that sauce on roasted halved eggplants in my cookbook; it&#8217;s really lovely with other roasted vegetables too (there&#8217;s a <a href="http://smittenkitchen.com/blog/2009/01/warm-butternut-squash-and-chickpea-salad/" rel="nofollow">warm butternut squash salad</a> on this site that uses a lemon-tahini dressing too). </p>
<p>Janice &#8212; Why did you peel them? I do this for <a href="http://smittenkitchen.com/blog/2013/01/ethereally-smooth-hummus/" rel="nofollow">hummus</a>, but certainly wouldn&#8217;t here. Plus, for roasting, having that skin is essential to getting them crackly/crisp.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-26T12:47:25-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816486">
						<span class="date">March 26, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:47 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816486#respond" data-commentid="816486" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816486" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to deb" aria-label="Reply to deb">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816486 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816487">
		<article id="div-comment-816487" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											michelle									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Had this for dinner tonight&#8230;delicious!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-26T19:35:24-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816487">
						<span class="date">March 26, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:35 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816487#respond" data-commentid="816487" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816487" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to michelle" aria-label="Reply to michelle">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816487 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816488">
		<article id="div-comment-816488" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Jenny									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>THIS WAS SO DELICIOUS!!! Everything I wanted last night for dinner. Thank you!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-27T08:34:32-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816488">
						<span class="date">March 27, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:34 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816488#respond" data-commentid="816488" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816488" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jenny" aria-label="Reply to Jenny">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816488 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816489">
		<article id="div-comment-816489" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											nora1									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Had this for dinner, it was great&#8230;I had no coriander for the chickpeas so subbed in a generous amount of za&#8217;atar, next time i&#8217;ll follow the recipe properly&#8230;Delicious anyway, and the tahini yoghurt is fantastic. Win.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-27T08:44:46-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816489">
						<span class="date">March 27, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:44 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816489#respond" data-commentid="816489" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816489" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to nora1" aria-label="Reply to nora1">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816489 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816490">
		<article id="div-comment-816490" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Lyn Napel									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Oh my gawd, this is the best thing I&#8217;ve made in ages, Deb! Easy to put together. Redolent with spices. Delicious! I cannot wait to get into the leftovers today. Maybe right after I finish this cup of coffee…</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-27T10:15:02-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816490">
						<span class="date">March 27, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">10:15 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816490#respond" data-commentid="816490" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816490" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lyn Napel" aria-label="Reply to Lyn Napel">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816490 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816491">
		<article id="div-comment-816491" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											anne									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made this for dinner last Night. I thought it was very good but my husband thought it was a bit bland, he did not care for it much. Just one note: is it supposed to be a bit soupy? I used the measurements but even when the chick peas were cooked there was a lot of liquid left.<br />
Just one word of caution for fellow cooks: 1 pound of dried chickpeas is A LOT of chickpeas. At least 6 generous helpings. Thanks for posting the recipe.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-27T11:14:02-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816491">
						<span class="date">March 27, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:14 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816491#respond" data-commentid="816491" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816491" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to anne" aria-label="Reply to anne">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816491 -->
	 </li>
	<ol class="children">
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-debsk bypostauthor even depth-2" id="comment-816492">
		<article id="div-comment-816492" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://smittenkitchen.com">deb</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Bland as in needed salt or spice? Or something else?, It&#8217;s not supposed to be soupy, although a little extra liquid is fine, but the amount of liquid dried beans will absorb is never an exact science; it can have to do with how old they were, how long they soaked, how much they absorbed when they soaked, etc. The liquid shouldn&#8217;t have too much effect; you can just scoop the beans with a slotted spoon. That said, these are estimates that have worked for me over the years with various soaking times. Re, serving size&#8230; I think we agree; I noted it for 6 generous servings.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-27T11:44:17-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816492">
						<span class="date">March 27, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:44 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816492#respond" data-commentid="816492" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816492" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to deb" aria-label="Reply to deb">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816492 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816493">
		<article id="div-comment-816493" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Allee									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made this last night and now I&#8217;m eating the cucumber tomato salad and chickpeas together for lunch.  I also added feta cheese and some olives.  Thanks for the recipe Deb!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-27T12:44:49-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816493">
						<span class="date">March 27, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:44 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816493#respond" data-commentid="816493" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816493" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Allee" aria-label="Reply to Allee">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816493 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816494">
		<article id="div-comment-816494" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.lollipoperie.com">Sarit</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>We do this at home too &#8211; taco night is a twice monthly mainstay, which almost always carries over into the next dinner thanks to so many leftovers (we are 2 people, I cook for 3+ every time). Then when we don&#8217;t feel like TexMex, we have &#8220;Mediterranean Night&#8221; , with pita, hummus, Israeli salad, chickpeas, tahini, the works. Looking forward to trying it your way!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-27T13:27:51-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816494">
						<span class="date">March 27, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:27 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816494#respond" data-commentid="816494" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816494" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Sarit" aria-label="Reply to Sarit">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816494 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816495">
		<article id="div-comment-816495" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Liisa									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Just had this for dinner. Amazing! Thanks for the inspiration and greetings from Helsinki :)</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-27T14:18:34-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816495">
						<span class="date">March 27, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">2:18 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816495#respond" data-commentid="816495" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816495" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Liisa" aria-label="Reply to Liisa">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816495 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816496">
		<article id="div-comment-816496" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Judith									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Nummers. Try this variation on the pita chips: brush the pita with oil, then sprinkle with za&#8217;atar (1 tablespoon fresh thyme, 1 tablespoon toasted sesame seeds, 1 teaspoons ground sumac, 1/4 teaspoon coarse salt) before baking.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-27T14:42:40-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816496">
						<span class="date">March 27, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">2:42 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816496#respond" data-commentid="816496" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816496" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Judith" aria-label="Reply to Judith">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816496 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816497">
		<article id="div-comment-816497" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											anne									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Deb, thanks for your response. My husband thought it lacked for spices. I however thought it was just right! Just reporting because I like to have other pple&#8217;s comments on how the dish was.<br />
Mine was very very soupy. Needed to be served in bowls. I soaked my dried beans for 24 hours &#8211; I would suggest only the cups of broth without the additional cup of water to other cooks, especially if to be used with the proposed pita chips. Ours would have gotten totally soggy if we had served them with the chickpeas and pitas on the same plate.<br />
Yes &#8211; I saw afterwards that you put &#8220;serves 6&#8221;. I guess I&#8217;m just concurring that even with our very healthy (glutinous) appetites, there were 6 servings.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-27T17:02:04-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816497">
						<span class="date">March 27, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">5:02 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816497#respond" data-commentid="816497" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816497" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to anne" aria-label="Reply to anne">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816497 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-debsk bypostauthor even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816498">
		<article id="div-comment-816498" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://smittenkitchen.com">deb</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>anne &#8212; Thanks for the feedback. (I was in a rush before and forgot my manners.) You are the second person to say that with 24 hours soaking, you had too much final liquid so I&#8217;m now seeing a pattern and will add an adjustment.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-27T17:34:27-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816498">
						<span class="date">March 27, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">5:34 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816498#respond" data-commentid="816498" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816498" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to deb" aria-label="Reply to deb">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816498 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816499">
		<article id="div-comment-816499" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Katie									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Just made this tonight. Absolutely delicious!! Thanks, Deb!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-28T14:58:29-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816499">
						<span class="date">March 28, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">2:58 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816499#respond" data-commentid="816499" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816499" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Katie" aria-label="Reply to Katie">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816499 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816500">
		<article id="div-comment-816500" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://10legsinthekitchen.com">10 Legs in the Kitchen</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Anything Chick pea for me!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-28T18:14:28-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816500">
						<span class="date">March 28, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">6:14 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816500#respond" data-commentid="816500" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816500" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to 10 Legs in the Kitchen" aria-label="Reply to 10 Legs in the Kitchen">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816500 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816501">
		<article id="div-comment-816501" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Britt									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Smitten Kitchen, I must say that your &#8216;Baked Chick Pease W/ Pita Chips And Yogurt&#8217; looks like HEAVEN! I love love love chick peas and I feel like I should try this. Thank you for always putting up your Recipes so that the rest of us can enjoy these healthy and delicious food with you. How do you come up with these things?? You&#8217;re a Chef when it comes to the kitchen, and if I had the money to make these things I would. But, I&#8217;m trying to save up for a car and my mom always says that she doesn&#8217;t want to buy anything, but wants me to eat healthy. I don&#8217;t have that typeof money, but she does. But really Thank You for sharing these delicious looking and tasting dishes.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-28T21:20:06-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816501">
						<span class="date">March 28, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:20 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816501#respond" data-commentid="816501" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816501" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Britt" aria-label="Reply to Britt">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816501 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816502">
		<article id="div-comment-816502" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Hillery									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Thanks, Deb, for a great recipe! Made it tonight for my family, and my normally picky son gobbled it up (along with the rest of us). That&#8217;s a major win in my book!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-28T22:44:49-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816502">
						<span class="date">March 28, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">10:44 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816502#respond" data-commentid="816502" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816502" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Hillery" aria-label="Reply to Hillery">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816502 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816503">
		<article id="div-comment-816503" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Michelle									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>A-MAY-ZING!!!  So delicious!  The combination of everything together is perfect!  Thank you for posting this!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-29T13:15:27-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816503">
						<span class="date">March 29, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:15 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816503#respond" data-commentid="816503" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816503" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Michelle" aria-label="Reply to Michelle">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816503 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816504">
		<article id="div-comment-816504" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											MS									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made this today for lunch, almost exactly as written.  (I can&#8217;t believe I had sumac hidden in the cupboard.)  I used chickpeas soaked for about 20 hours and found that four cups of broth was just about perfect.  We ate it nacho-style for lunch.  To the rest of the pot, I then added roasted eggplant cubes, a can of drained, fire-roasted tomatoes, and some parsley.  I put it back in the oven to cook for about 30 minutes.  Voila!  A whole new dish for later this week!  Thanks so much for the inspiration.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-29T14:43:54-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816504">
						<span class="date">March 29, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">2:43 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816504#respond" data-commentid="816504" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816504" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to MS" aria-label="Reply to MS">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816504 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816505">
		<article id="div-comment-816505" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.honeywhatscooking.com/">Honey, What&#8217;s Cooking?</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Man, you are detailed.  I love it.  My mom often makes Indian chickpeas, I&#8217;m gonna see how long she soaks it as well.  I don&#8217;t think she&#8217;s ever baked chickpeas in a dutchoven, this is cool.  She pressure cooks it.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-29T15:13:29-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816505">
						<span class="date">March 29, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">3:13 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816505#respond" data-commentid="816505" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816505" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Honey, What&#039;s Cooking?" aria-label="Reply to Honey, What&#039;s Cooking?">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816505 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816506">
		<article id="div-comment-816506" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Mac									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>We made this on Friday for dinner and it is one of the BEST meals we&#8217;ve had in a long time.  For others who may be making this with dried beans they&#8217;ve had in the pantry for over a year (like me)&#8211;it did take me about 30 minutes longer than recommended to cook them after soaking for only 4 hours.  (About 1h 45m.)</p>
<p>We ate the beans with fresh pitas (instead of making chips) and a green hot sauce called zhuk. I roughly followed the recipe here, using jalapeños and serranos:  <a href="http://humus101.com/EN/tag/zhuk/" rel="nofollow ugc">http://humus101.com/EN/tag/zhuk/</a>.  (This is very close to the green hot sauce they serve at The Hummus Place.  It is so so good.  I can&#8217;t believe I waited so long to try to replicate it!)</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-29T17:00:21-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816506">
						<span class="date">March 29, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">5:00 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816506#respond" data-commentid="816506" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816506" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Mac" aria-label="Reply to Mac">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816506 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816507">
		<article id="div-comment-816507" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											dominique									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Made it for dinner tonight using pita chips on the bottom for crispy texture. When the sauce from the beans and toppings comes together at the end of the meal, it is absolutely delicious. Very reminiscent of another favorite of ours, your sweet potatoes with celery/cranberry/shallot salsa. Thanks for helping me find great ideas for a vegetarian daughter.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-29T19:26:07-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816507">
						<span class="date">March 29, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:26 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816507#respond" data-commentid="816507" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816507" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to dominique" aria-label="Reply to dominique">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816507 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816508">
		<article id="div-comment-816508" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Kaitlin									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Wow &#8211; I think I&#8217;ve been undercooking my chickpeas my whole life. I had no idea they could taste this good! I made two-thirds the recipe (because 1 lb of chickpeas is a LOT of chickpeas) but kept the spices the same, and it worked out beautifully. </p>
<p>I love that this recipe is a sum of many smaller recipes, which can each be eaten on their own!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-29T19:31:39-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816508">
						<span class="date">March 29, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:31 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816508#respond" data-commentid="816508" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816508" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kaitlin" aria-label="Reply to Kaitlin">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816508 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816509">
		<article id="div-comment-816509" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Lindsay									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>How long will the tahini yogurt sauce last in the fridge?</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-30T12:54:26-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816509">
						<span class="date">March 30, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:54 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816509#respond" data-commentid="816509" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816509" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lindsay" aria-label="Reply to Lindsay">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816509 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816510">
		<article id="div-comment-816510" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Katrin									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This was so good! Will definitely be making it again!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-30T13:04:49-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816510">
						<span class="date">March 30, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:04 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816510#respond" data-commentid="816510" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816510" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Katrin" aria-label="Reply to Katrin">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816510 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816511">
		<article id="div-comment-816511" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Becky									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made the chickpeas and lemon-tahini yogurt sauce this weekend and I cannot get enough. This is great for work lunches, too &#8211; I put a few handfuls of pre-shredded broccoli/carrots bagged mix in my tupperware, put some beans on top, and then a few spoons of dressing and a soft-boiled egg on top of that. Very yummy.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-30T13:27:05-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816511">
						<span class="date">March 30, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:27 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816511#respond" data-commentid="816511" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816511" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Becky" aria-label="Reply to Becky">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816511 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816512">
		<article id="div-comment-816512" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Cara									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made this to take to the office for lunch and it has totally made my week!  I bumped up the spices and the garlic (maybe almost doubled them?) and it was delicious.  Complete recipe win :)</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-30T14:17:10-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816512">
						<span class="date">March 30, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">2:17 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816512#respond" data-commentid="816512" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816512" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Cara" aria-label="Reply to Cara">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816512 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816513">
		<article id="div-comment-816513" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Jasmine									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I just tasted the chickpeas after they came out of the oven. I used homemade chicken stock. They are so good I can&#8217;t believe it. Thank you so so much! To your health, Deb!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-30T17:56:14-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816513">
						<span class="date">March 30, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">5:56 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816513#respond" data-commentid="816513" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816513" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jasmine" aria-label="Reply to Jasmine">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816513 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816514">
		<article id="div-comment-816514" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Beth									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Just made this tonight.  Turned out great.  I used canned chickpeas, and the 1.5 cups of water/broth was too much, but I just scooped them out with a holed spoon to drain.  Also, this is great for kids.  My son hates yogurt, so he used coriander chutney on his chickpeas instead.  Anything where my kids can assemble their dinner to their specifications is always great.  A couple more things, the pine nuts really got lost in the flavor/texture of the dish, so I won&#8217;t use them next time.  Also, I was too lazy to run out and get tahini, and I knew I&#8217;d have a lot of leftover with nothing to use it for, so my yogurt was tahini-less.  Still great topping though.  I also burned my pita chips, so I&#8217;ll probably just buy a big bag next time (I&#8217;m not above taking shortcuts!).  Thanks Deb.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-30T18:37:14-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816514">
						<span class="date">March 30, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">6:37 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816514#respond" data-commentid="816514" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816514" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Beth" aria-label="Reply to Beth">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816514 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816515">
		<article id="div-comment-816515" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Flavia									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I just made this tonight and wow, it turned out fantastic! The flavors are a party in your mouth! Thanks for this keeper!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-30T23:52:10-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816515">
						<span class="date">March 30, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:52 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816515#respond" data-commentid="816515" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816515" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Flavia" aria-label="Reply to Flavia">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816515 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816516">
		<article id="div-comment-816516" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Laura									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>4 words: CROCK POT THOSE LEGUMES!  If flavor isn&#8217;t a big enough argument in favor of using dried, how &#8217;bout price?  When I make hummus, I throw a big, rinsed bunch in salted water in the crock pot (often overnight) and, with almost no effort, have some to use, some to eat, and some to freeze.</p>
<p>For the working crew that needs to feed little hungry mouths shortly after getting home, it seems like your recipe here, Deb, is a perfect candidate for a crock pot adaptation.  I know spices can get sadly muted in a crock, but dry toasting them briefly on the stove before adding, then tossing in another pinch or two right at the end keeps the depth and livens things back up.  From there, perhaps the last thing to work out is the crockville ratio for spice/chick pea/veg stock.  </p>
<p>What do you think, Deb, et al?</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-31T10:31:05-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816516">
						<span class="date">March 31, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">10:31 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816516#respond" data-commentid="816516" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816516" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Laura" aria-label="Reply to Laura">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816516 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816517">
		<article id="div-comment-816517" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Megan									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Hi Deb! I&#8217;m sincerely hoping that you will post recipes like those you mentioned in the first paragraph! I&#8217;m always looking for ways to make beans more flavorful/exciting/appetizing&#8230;</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-31T15:47:24-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816517">
						<span class="date">March 31, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">3:47 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816517#respond" data-commentid="816517" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816517" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Megan" aria-label="Reply to Megan">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816517 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-debsk bypostauthor even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816518">
		<article id="div-comment-816518" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://smittenkitchen.com">deb</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Megan &#8212; Thanks; I should really write these ideas down for the next time I&#8217;m in an idea drought. :)</p>
<p>Laura &#8212; Yes, definitely definitely is. If only I had finally taken mine down from the shelf and tested this there, I think it would have been helpful. Soon, I hope.</p>
<p>Lindsay &#8212; Definitely a week, maybe a little longer? (Safely, though, a week.)</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-31T17:16:47-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816518">
						<span class="date">March 31, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">5:16 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816518#respond" data-commentid="816518" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816518" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to deb" aria-label="Reply to deb">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816518 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816519">
		<article id="div-comment-816519" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Hadley									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Made it! Man have I got a lot of chickpeas now. It was fun to make, though! I used dried beans, soaked for 18 hrs. and they baked for 45 minutes. Pretty delicious!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-31T19:07:17-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816519">
						<span class="date">March 31, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:07 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816519#respond" data-commentid="816519" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816519" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Hadley" aria-label="Reply to Hadley">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816519 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816520">
		<article id="div-comment-816520" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Flavia									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This was fantastic. Especially the fact that it&#8217;s meatless but you totally don&#8217;t feel like you&#8217;re skipping anything&#8230;</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-31T19:45:16-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816520">
						<span class="date">March 31, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:45 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816520#respond" data-commentid="816520" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816520" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Flavia" aria-label="Reply to Flavia">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816520 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816521">
		<article id="div-comment-816521" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Katie									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I just made this for dinner this evening and it&#8217;s incredible!!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-03-31T20:32:41-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816521">
						<span class="date">March 31, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:32 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816521#respond" data-commentid="816521" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816521" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Katie" aria-label="Reply to Katie">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816521 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816522">
		<article id="div-comment-816522" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Chelsea									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Hi Deb &#8211; thanks so much for posting this recipe &#8211; my partner and I loved it, and our 4-year old ATE IT ALL! Congratulations &#8211; a winner! ;)  We will be making it regularly now.</p>
<p>The leftovers also made for superb lunches &#8211; I&#8217;m trying to do a food diary right now, so I easily portioned everything out into mason jars, except the pita bits, took it to work, then assembled it there and was so, so happy that I did. Fresh, filling, balanced lunch. Thank you!!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-01T14:58:37-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816522">
						<span class="date">April 1, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">2:58 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816522#respond" data-commentid="816522" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816522" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Chelsea" aria-label="Reply to Chelsea">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816522 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816523">
		<article id="div-comment-816523" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Ingrid									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Hi Deb. I made this last night and it was great. I have *never* seen my daughter ask for more helpings of any dish, and that includes pancakes. So thank you! There&#8217;s something I&#8217;m curious about, though: do you think that baking this dish in the oven provides a certain benefit that would be absent if this were simmered (covered) on the stove? I&#8217;m wondering what would happen if I skipped the oven step next time.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-01T17:46:26-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816523">
						<span class="date">April 1, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">5:46 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816523#respond" data-commentid="816523" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816523" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Ingrid" aria-label="Reply to Ingrid">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816523 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816524">
		<article id="div-comment-816524" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Lindsay									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Pretty sure this will be for breakfast tomorrow in addition to dinner tonight. Maybe lunch, too, but that&#8217;s only if I have enough (because you guys, i&#8217;m INHALING it as I type!).</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-01T18:04:25-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816524">
						<span class="date">April 1, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">6:04 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816524#respond" data-commentid="816524" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816524" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lindsay" aria-label="Reply to Lindsay">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816524 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816525">
		<article id="div-comment-816525" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Cindy									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Chiming in to say this was great. I&#8217;m not a fan of raw tomatoes or cucumbers so I replaced that with a spicy date chutney but otherwise made this very close to as-written (used Stacy&#8217;s pita chips and doubled all spices). It was phenomenal &#8211; sweet and salty and savory all at once. My omnivorous partner said, &#8220;this doesn&#8217;t taste like it&#8217;s a &#8220;beans!&#8221; dish.&#8221;</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-01T19:44:45-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816525">
						<span class="date">April 1, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:44 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816525#respond" data-commentid="816525" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816525" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Cindy" aria-label="Reply to Cindy">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816525 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816526">
		<article id="div-comment-816526" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Heather									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>My chickpea loving 6 year old declared this &#8220;chickpea heaven&#8221;  :)  the rest of us loved it too!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-01T19:45:02-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816526">
						<span class="date">April 1, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:45 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816526#respond" data-commentid="816526" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816526" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Heather" aria-label="Reply to Heather">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816526 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816527">
		<article id="div-comment-816527" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Sydney									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I did mine with some cilantro, and a cucumber onion vinegar slaw type thing! What a meal!!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-01T20:07:38-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816527">
						<span class="date">April 1, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:07 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816527#respond" data-commentid="816527" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816527" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Sydney" aria-label="Reply to Sydney">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816527 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816528">
		<article id="div-comment-816528" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											RJP									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>In low carb mode so served this over some lightly seasoned sauteed spinach and it worked out great. Also, had to replace the cucumber with a yellow pepper and it did not disappoint.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-01T21:16:36-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816528">
						<span class="date">April 1, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:16 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816528#respond" data-commentid="816528" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816528" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to RJP" aria-label="Reply to RJP">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816528 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816529">
		<article id="div-comment-816529" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://walnutglenbarn.com">Kelly Culler</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Okay Deb, these are the bomb.com!  Just made them for supper with what I had on hand.  We all loved them husband, 16 year old son and myself.  Husband took some to work tonight and I&#8217;ve got more for lunch tomorrow.  This is the cure for the hummus fallback.  Thanks!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-02T18:22:54-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816529">
						<span class="date">April 2, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">6:22 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816529#respond" data-commentid="816529" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816529" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kelly Culler" aria-label="Reply to Kelly Culler">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816529 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816530">
		<article id="div-comment-816530" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											KimP									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Simply quite delicious! Super-satisfyingly so. Best dinner we&#8217;ve had at our house in awhile. Vegan version was perfection. Thank you, Deb!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-03T19:57:22-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816530">
						<span class="date">April 3, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:57 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816530#respond" data-commentid="816530" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816530" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to KimP" aria-label="Reply to KimP">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816530 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816531">
		<article id="div-comment-816531" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Chum									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Deb, thanks for all the great recipes! There are as many variations to Lebanese recipes as there are villages in Lebanon. My family used very little cumin, no cilantro, and TONS of cinnamon and seven-spice (you can get a wonderful version of this at the Middle Eastern spice store across from Sahadi&#8217;s on Atlantic Ave in Bk). So, we would eat this with cinnamon and maybe some allspice or seven-spice, with chopped parsley &amp; mint. I also wonder if chopped dates or even chopped booked eggs would be nice on top? I love that your creativity sparks my own. Best thing about this blog. Have a great holiday weekend! xo</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-03T23:21:53-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816531">
						<span class="date">April 3, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:21 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816531#respond" data-commentid="816531" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816531" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Chum" aria-label="Reply to Chum">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816531 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816532">
