				<b class="fn author-name">
											Chum									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Ha. &#8220;Boiled&#8221; eggs, not &#8220;booked.&#8221; Damn iPhone.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-03T23:22:49-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816532">
						<span class="date">April 3, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:22 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816532#respond" data-commentid="816532" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816532" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Chum" aria-label="Reply to Chum">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816532 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816533">
		<article id="div-comment-816533" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Shari									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Deb, I made this is a side dish for Passover seder and served it with matzoh (Shmerer). It was delicious and a great change from the ordinary. Thanks.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-05T13:55:29-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816533">
						<span class="date">April 5, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:55 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816533#respond" data-commentid="816533" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816533" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Shari" aria-label="Reply to Shari">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
