	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816535">
		<article id="div-comment-816535" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Susan									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I&#8217;m making this for the second time tonight. Thanks, Deb. I love your site!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-07T17:43:38-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816535">
						<span class="date">April 7, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">5:43 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816535#respond" data-commentid="816535" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816535" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Susan" aria-label="Reply to Susan">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816535 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816536">
		<article id="div-comment-816536" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.lt-green.blogspot.com">Catlin</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made this last week and it was a huge hit! Very easy; I had a friend drop by and she loved it.</p>
<p>When I ran out of pita chips, the chickpeas were also great over rice and in a tostada shell, which I guess doesn&#8217;t quite get beyond the Tex-Mex thing&#8230;</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-07T18:22:54-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816536">
						<span class="date">April 7, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">6:22 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816536#respond" data-commentid="816536" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816536" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Catlin" aria-label="Reply to Catlin">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816536 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816537">
		<article id="div-comment-816537" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Megan									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This was delicious!  Fun to make with a hungry 4 year old too, as he could just stand at the counter and eat yogurt and cucumber relish while I worked, so much better than having bunny crackers and a cheese stick.  I used Zatar in the beans and on the chips.  I forgot the pine nuts, but we did top it with parsley and cilantro, and I wouldn&#8217;t skip that step, it really brightens the whole thing up.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-08T08:03:18-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816537">
						<span class="date">April 8, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:03 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816537#respond" data-commentid="816537" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816537" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Megan" aria-label="Reply to Megan">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816537 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816538">
		<article id="div-comment-816538" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Alana									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Hey Deb, since I got your cookbook for x-mas, I have basically made Smitten kitchen recipes every other night. Reading your blog is one of my faaaavorite things to do :) Quick question: how long exactly do dried chick peas last? Last time I made mine, the little white skins all came off the peas and made for a pretty ugly bowl of chickpeas! Someone said it might be because they were old. How long do they keep?</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-08T09:23:51-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816538">
						<span class="date">April 8, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:23 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816538#respond" data-commentid="816538" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816538" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Alana" aria-label="Reply to Alana">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816538 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-debsk bypostauthor odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816539">
		<article id="div-comment-816539" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://smittenkitchen.com">deb</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Alana &#8212; I don&#8217;t see why they can&#8217;t last a year or even up to two if in a cool dry place, well-sealed. Of course, they&#8217;ll be better in the first year, and they&#8217;ll also be better if they weren&#8217;t a year old when they got to your grocery store. I&#8217;m not sure if the skin coming off is always about age; this is just a property of a lot of chickpeas, though I suppose it&#8217;s more likely to happen if they&#8217;re quite old.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-08T11:44:37-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816539">
						<span class="date">April 8, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:44 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816539#respond" data-commentid="816539" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816539" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to deb" aria-label="Reply to deb">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816539 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816540">
		<article id="div-comment-816540" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://stephdownsouth.blogspot.com">Stephanie</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Made this for dinner (and lunch the next day) and will definitely make again (and again and again). Using canned chickpeas worked fine. I had some homemade tzatziki sauce leftover from earlier in the week &#8211; I topped my beans and pita chips with that, some feta crumbles and chopped tomatoes. Delicious!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-08T14:33:40-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816540">
						<span class="date">April 8, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">2:33 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816540#respond" data-commentid="816540" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816540" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Stephanie" aria-label="Reply to Stephanie">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816540 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816541">
		<article id="div-comment-816541" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Hadley									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This just in!!! I had leftover sauce and leftover chickpeas, and I just sauteed some spinach with garlic, topped it with chickpeas and a soft-boiled egg, then doused that all in the sauce and OH MY GOD. It was better, I&#8217;d dare say, than my original dish. YUM SO EXCITED FOR LEFTOVERS.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-08T20:37:12-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816541">
						<span class="date">April 8, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:37 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816541#respond" data-commentid="816541" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816541" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Hadley" aria-label="Reply to Hadley">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816541 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816542">
		<article id="div-comment-816542" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.whatscookingatdinnerthyme.com">Deb</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This looks amazing!  Can&#8217;t wait to try it!  (I&#8217;m thinking Saturday).  As always, your pics are amazing as well!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-09T08:45:08-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816542">
						<span class="date">April 9, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:45 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816542#respond" data-commentid="816542" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816542" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Deb" aria-label="Reply to Deb">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816542 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816543">
		<article id="div-comment-816543" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Amber									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This was prepared and destroyed for dinner last night!  Absolutely declicious.  Pie shell is chilling in the fridge as I speak, ready to be filled with your chocolate pudding pie :)</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-10T09:09:41-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816543">
						<span class="date">April 10, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:09 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816543#respond" data-commentid="816543" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816543" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Amber" aria-label="Reply to Amber">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816543 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816544">
		<article id="div-comment-816544" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Lizzie									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I just made these for dinner, and i found scooping all of the toppings on top of the baked pita chips made them soggy pretty quickly. I think next time, I would prefer to create a bowl of everything, and then scoop things with the pita chips, kind of like a chips and dip situation.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-10T10:57:28-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816544">
						<span class="date">April 10, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">10:57 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816544#respond" data-commentid="816544" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816544" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lizzie" aria-label="Reply to Lizzie">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816544 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816545">
		<article id="div-comment-816545" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Terry Wood									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made this last night and it was delicious.  Thanks.  Unlike your previous commenter, I like Better Than Bullion vegetable stock base.  I guess it is just a matter of &#8220;taste&#8221;.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-10T11:19:38-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816545">
						<span class="date">April 10, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:19 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816545#respond" data-commentid="816545" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816545" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Terry Wood" aria-label="Reply to Terry Wood">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816545 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816546">
		<article id="div-comment-816546" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.lennaesworld.com">Lennae</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Yum, Yum, Yum! Can&#8217;t wait to try this recipe out!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-11T07:46:32-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816546">
						<span class="date">April 11, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:46 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816546#respond" data-commentid="816546" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816546" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lennae" aria-label="Reply to Lennae">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816546 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816547">
		<article id="div-comment-816547" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Leslie									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>They&#8217;re in the oven now! Can&#8217;t wait! Thanks for another great read and another great recipe.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-11T19:20:07-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816547">
						<span class="date">April 11, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:20 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816547#respond" data-commentid="816547" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816547" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Leslie" aria-label="Reply to Leslie">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816547 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816548">
		<article id="div-comment-816548" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Michele (Washington)									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Really enjoyed and made the following modifications. Used dried beans I made In the pressure cooker with 2 inches of kombu. I use extra water when I cook beans as when they sit in the fridge it gets soaked up. In this case I used right away and just stirred in the Kombu and did not need any broth. My beans were a little more done then canned, but I still cooked for 30 mins. The dish was saucy but I just scoped them out. Rather than the Chips I made pita sandwiches. Cut I half, spread some of the lemon-tahini sauce, romain lettuce, beans and topped with dressed cucumber and tomatoes. Skipped the pine nuts,  tip for veg broth- I save all my veggie peels (on, kale etc) during the week in a ziplock bag in the fridge and then throw in a pot with a bay leaf and simmer an hour,  fresh stock every week,</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-14T00:38:24-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816548">
						<span class="date">April 14, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:38 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816548#respond" data-commentid="816548" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816548" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Michele (Washington)" aria-label="Reply to Michele (Washington)">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816548 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816549">
		<article id="div-comment-816549" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Hallie									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Made this tonight. Phenomenal!! Even my carnivore boyfriend, who normally whines about eating anything not covere in bacon, had seconds! I added some feta and completely forgot about the pine nuts until I was halfway finished with my plate. And at that point, much more important things were happening.  Needless to say, they weren&#8217;t missed.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-19T22:02:33-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816549">
						<span class="date">April 19, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">10:02 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816549#respond" data-commentid="816549" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816549" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Hallie" aria-label="Reply to Hallie">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816549 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816550">
		<article id="div-comment-816550" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											lauren									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made this over the weekend and halved the recipe since there were only two of us. Very tasty!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-20T10:31:06-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816550">
						<span class="date">April 20, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">10:31 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816550#respond" data-commentid="816550" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816550" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to lauren" aria-label="Reply to lauren">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816550 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816551">
		<article id="div-comment-816551" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://myblueandwhitekitchen.com">Sini</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This looks so good! Can&#8217;t wait to make it. I bet it&#8217;s a crowd pleaser.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-20T12:17:11-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816551">
						<span class="date">April 20, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:17 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816551#respond" data-commentid="816551" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816551" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Sini" aria-label="Reply to Sini">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816551 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816552">
		<article id="div-comment-816552" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Amy									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Finally made this; it was a hit. I made all of the &#8220;fixings&#8221; you listed, as well. Thanks for a great meal!  And the broth amount (1 1/2 c.) with the canned chick peas was perfect. Can&#8217;t wait to enjoy the leftovers tomorrow&#8230;just need to make a bit more of the relish.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-20T22:29:32-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816552">
						<span class="date">April 20, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">10:29 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816552#respond" data-commentid="816552" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816552" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Amy" aria-label="Reply to Amy">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816552 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816553">
		<article id="div-comment-816553" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Melaura									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Hi all, I made this last night and it was delicious. I brined 1 lb of dry chickpeas for 24 hours (using about 3 teaspoons salt) and they came out lovely and tender. </p>
<p>Thanks for your blog and your work, Deb, I&#8217;ve been reading and cooking since 2007 :)</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-23T14:12:22-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816553">
						<span class="date">April 23, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">2:12 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816553#respond" data-commentid="816553" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816553" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Melaura" aria-label="Reply to Melaura">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816553 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816554">
		<article id="div-comment-816554" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Allison									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made this tonight and it was really good. I split the recipe in half and used 2 cans of chickpeas. I forgot that I was halving the recipe and used the full spice amount.  I thought the spice level was good.  I think if if I made the full recipe then I would double the spices.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-04-29T19:37:02-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816554">
						<span class="date">April 29, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:37 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816554#respond" data-commentid="816554" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816554" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Allison" aria-label="Reply to Allison">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816554 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816555">
		<article id="div-comment-816555" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Sarah									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I&#8217;ve made this twice since I read this. It&#8217;s sooooo very delicious! A new favorite!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-05-03T08:29:19-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816555">
						<span class="date">May 3, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:29 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816555#respond" data-commentid="816555" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816555" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Sarah" aria-label="Reply to Sarah">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816555 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816556">
		<article id="div-comment-816556" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Nanda									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I don&#8217;t understand why you think this would only keep a couple days in the fridge. With vegetable broth, there are no meat products, so shouldn&#8217;t it keep more like 4-5 days? Maybe it would need added water from the fridge to the table, but I shouldn&#8217;t think it&#8217;d go bad quickly.</p>
<p>Anyhow, I accidentally made the full recipe (instead of 1/2) last night, so I&#8217;m going to see how long the chickpeas and dressing last in the fridge. In addition, I put some of the chickpeas in the freezer, so we&#8217;ll see how that works out as well.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-05-04T15:31:31-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816556">
						<span class="date">May 4, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">3:31 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816556#respond" data-commentid="816556" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816556" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Nanda" aria-label="Reply to Nanda">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816556 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816557">
		<article id="div-comment-816557" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Elisa									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Hi Deb, This sounds great! I&#8217;d like to make it tomorrow and use some leftover pita bread that I&#8217;ve frozen. Any idea if I should thaw it before making the chips? Or just toss them in the over frozen and bake for a longer amount of time?<br />
Thanks!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-05-05T11:40:39-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816557">
						<span class="date">May 5, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:40 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816557#respond" data-commentid="816557" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816557" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Elisa" aria-label="Reply to Elisa">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816557 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-debsk bypostauthor even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816558">
		<article id="div-comment-816558" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://smittenkitchen.com">deb</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Elisa &#8212; You can toast the pita bread right from the freezer.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-05-07T21:40:29-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816558">
						<span class="date">May 7, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:40 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816558#respond" data-commentid="816558" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816558" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to deb" aria-label="Reply to deb">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816558 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816559">
		<article id="div-comment-816559" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											vivian									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Made this last night for dinner, and it was so good! I rarely make anything more than once or twice, since there are so many fabulous recipes to try, but this will for sure be made again at our house. Thanks so much for a wonderful recipe.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-05-10T12:37:50-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816559">
						<span class="date">May 10, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:37 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816559#respond" data-commentid="816559" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816559" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to vivian" aria-label="Reply to vivian">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816559 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816560">
		<article id="div-comment-816560" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://anna7407.blogspot.com/">Chip</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Indeed very appealing in taste and texture chips. However, the temperature had little tweak the 100 alloy is not enough. It is a pity that so hard to track down this veggie worth a sin</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-05-25T04:14:53-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816560">
						<span class="date">May 25, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">4:14 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816560#respond" data-commentid="816560" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816560" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Chip" aria-label="Reply to Chip">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816560 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816561">
		<article id="div-comment-816561" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Fatimah									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This looks amazing! That salad you made is what we call in Iran, salad shirazi. Something that we use in cooking here, is ver juice (made with unripe grapes). Try adding a splash or two of that to your salad next time &#8211; if you can find it, I don&#8217;t know who available it is in the us- along with a bit of dried crushed mint. Delish!</p>
<p>You can also make ver juice yourself. Just find seedless unripe grapes (the tiny round ones are the best) and juice them! Using them whole in eggplant stews is also heavenly, we keep them in our freezer year long</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-05-25T08:33:42-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816561">
						<span class="date">May 25, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:33 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816561#respond" data-commentid="816561" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816561" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Fatimah" aria-label="Reply to Fatimah">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816561 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816562">
		<article id="div-comment-816562" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://smittenkitchen.com">Liz</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>We really, really loved this! It is truly addictive! For once, I really didn&#8217;t do that much different. I did use some mint instead of parlsey (which was delightful!) and walnuts instead of pinenuts (didn&#8217;t have any). I think the pinenuts would be better. ;)</p>
<p>Nice work-I think this would be a great party plate! Thanks!!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-06-04T20:47:30-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816562">
						<span class="date">June 4, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:47 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816562#respond" data-commentid="816562" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816562" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Liz" aria-label="Reply to Liz">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816562 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816563">
		<article id="div-comment-816563" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Lore									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I just had to come by and leave a comment for this recipe, I can&#8217;t believe I haven&#8217;t yet. The day you posted this I got so enthusiastic about this recipe, I immediately made it the day after. Ever since it&#8217;s one of my favorite go-to meals. It&#8217;s surprisingly quick to throw together! First time making it was a bit of a hassle because I don&#8217;t have a very big oven, I couldn&#8217;t put both the chickpeas and the pita&#8217;s in at the same time. So the second time making it I decided to just leave the chickpeas on the stove on low heat in a Dutch oven. It actually didn&#8217;t make the recipe taste or feel different to me, so that&#8217;s how I&#8217;ve been making it since. Thank you, thank you, thank you for this recipe :)</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-06-18T09:00:52-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816563">
						<span class="date">June 18, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:00 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816563#respond" data-commentid="816563" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816563" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lore" aria-label="Reply to Lore">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816563 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816564">
		<article id="div-comment-816564" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Liz									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Such a delicious and satisfying meal!! I made a different yogurt sauce because I am not a huge fan of tahini (I made traditional tzatziki with Greek yogurt, cucumber, mint, salt, and pepper). Your recipes never fail me and my husband. My 11 month old is now eyeing everything we eat and wants to try. She will be a Smitten Kitchen baby for sure! :)</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-07-11T12:43:59-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816564">
						<span class="date">July 11, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:43 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816564#respond" data-commentid="816564" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816564" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Liz" aria-label="Reply to Liz">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816564 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816565">
		<article id="div-comment-816565" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											APS									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This makes a lot, and just to switch it up for lunches I put some in a bowl, smashed it with half an avocado, and smeared the mixture on toast. Delicious.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-10-01T12:16:12-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816565">
						<span class="date">October 1, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:16 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816565#respond" data-commentid="816565" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816565" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to APS" aria-label="Reply to APS">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816565 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816566">
		<article id="div-comment-816566" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Hannah									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>So good and so fast to make (I used canned chickpeas) &#8211; and as the person above me said, it makes a lot. The tahini sauce and tomato salad are perfect with it. Excellent vegetarian meal.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-10-08T21:17:13-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816566">
						<span class="date">October 8, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:17 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816566#respond" data-commentid="816566" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816566" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Hannah" aria-label="Reply to Hannah">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816566 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816567">
		<article id="div-comment-816567" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											T									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>A few questions as I prepare to make this for a potluck:</p>
<p>a) Can this be made in advance/refrigerated(/reheated)?<br />
b) I don&#8217;t own a heavy pot! I own &#8230; a cast-iron pan, and then some regular pots. Could I do the stove portion in a regular pot, and then transfer to e.g. a pyrex for the oven portion?</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-10-11T14:12:04-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816567">
						<span class="date">October 11, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">2:12 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816567#respond" data-commentid="816567" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816567" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to T" aria-label="Reply to T">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816567 -->
	 </li>
	<ol class="children">
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-debsk bypostauthor even depth-2" id="comment-816568">
		<article id="div-comment-816568" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://smittenkitchen.com">deb</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>T &#8212; Yes and yes.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2015-10-12T12:56:06-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816568">
						<span class="date">October 12, 2015</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:56 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816568#respond" data-commentid="816568" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816568" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to deb" aria-label="Reply to deb">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816568 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816569">
		<article id="div-comment-816569" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.gneissspice.com">Beth ~ Gneiss Spice</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Wow! Middle eastern food is my favorite (all the spices) and this recipe was just recommended to me. I&#8217;m on a food making binge as we&#8217;re expecting a baby in a few days.  Maybe this will be our last &#8220;pre-baby&#8221; meal.  :)  Also at the end of a kitchen renovation—so I made this in the crock pot.  Probably a little more souped than baked, but still absolutely delicious.  P.S. Used both paprika and sumac. How can you choose?</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2016-02-06T09:25:27-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816569">
						<span class="date">February 6, 2016</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:25 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816569#respond" data-commentid="816569" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816569" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Beth ~ Gneiss Spice" aria-label="Reply to Beth ~ Gneiss Spice">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816569 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816570">
		<article id="div-comment-816570" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Maria									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I&#8217;m making this for dinner (again!) tonight. I added a little mint to the relish &#8211; delish!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2016-03-10T14:15:53-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816570">
						<span class="date">March 10, 2016</span>
						at						<span class="time">2:15 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816570#respond" data-commentid="816570" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816570" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Maria" aria-label="Reply to Maria">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816570 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-816571">
		<article id="div-comment-816571" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Sarah									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Just made this tonight! It was absolutely delicious. One of my favorite all-time meals. I love the yummy savory roastedness of the chickpeas against the freshness of the relish&#8230;and the yogurt is to die for! I&#8217;m so glad there are leftovers! So many wonderful flavors!!!!!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2016-04-06T20:35:40-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816571">
						<span class="date">April 6, 2016</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:35 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816571#respond" data-commentid="816571" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816571" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Sarah" aria-label="Reply to Sarah">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816571 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-816572">
		<article id="div-comment-816572" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.manineeskitchen.com">Maninee</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>chickpeas are very good for health. This is like some chatpata dish. I will to love to try it. Thanks for sharing.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2016-04-23T11:28:04-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-816572">
						<span class="date">April 23, 2016</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:28 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=816572#respond" data-commentid="816572" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-816572" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Maninee" aria-label="Reply to Maninee">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-816572 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-835640">
		<article id="div-comment-835640" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://foodrecipesforindians.wordpress.com">yummyfoodrecipesindia</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Awesome food!! Want to prepare this healthy and tasty food recipe to my dinner :). Will give an attempt.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2016-07-15T02:31:38-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-835640">
						<span class="date">July 15, 2016</span>
						at						<span class="time">2:31 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=835640#respond" data-commentid="835640" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-835640" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to yummyfoodrecipesindia" aria-label="Reply to yummyfoodrecipesindia">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-835640 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-843514">
		<article id="div-comment-843514" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Clare									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made this last night and wanted to say it was SO delicious. Unbelievably so for such humble ingredients. Thank you. Today I reheated the leftover chickpeas, made a fresh batch of tomato salad, and plated the chickpeas with the salad, some yoghurt and added avocado and a crispy egg fried in olive oil and paprika for my brunch. It was great. Will be making this again and again. Xx</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2016-08-12T08:46:25-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-843514">
						<span class="date">August 12, 2016</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:46 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=843514#respond" data-commentid="843514" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-843514" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Clare" aria-label="Reply to Clare">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-843514 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-860730">
		<article id="div-comment-860730" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://timetoreboot.wordpress.com">Lisa</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Omg this was so delicious! Thank you!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2016-10-18T20:11:01-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-860730">
						<span class="date">October 18, 2016</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:11 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=860730#respond" data-commentid="860730" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-860730" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lisa" aria-label="Reply to Lisa">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-860730 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-865263">
		<article id="div-comment-865263" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Lori									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made this tonight, and it was a household hit. My husband had seconds (I shamelessly piled my plate high and ended up stuffed.) We did a deconstructed version for my 2 year old. He dipped everything in the lemon tahini yogurt dressing and cleaned his plate.</p>
<p>I soaked my chickpeas for about 5 hours, and ended up needing to cook them for as long as the 3 hour soak directions. I made the cucumber tomato relish, and added red bell pepper because I had it on hand. And in the chickpea base, instead of hot sauce I minced up a jalapeño (also because I had one) and threw it into the sautéed onions when I added the garlic. Oh, and I sprinkled flaked sea salt on the pita. The bigger pieces of salt on the chips were really tasty. </p>
<p>This is definitely going into the regular rotation. And I&#8217;m making lots of plans for that yogurt dressing.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2016-11-05T21:57:18-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-865263">
						<span class="date">November 5, 2016</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:57 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=865263#respond" data-commentid="865263" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-865263" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lori" aria-label="Reply to Lori">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-865263 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-887278">
		<article id="div-comment-887278" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Penni									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I do something like this &#8211; a lot using store bought or home made labneh with evoo and za&#8217;taar and pocket-less pitta triangles.  I am going to bite the bullet &#8211; prepare dried chickpeas &#8211; follow your recipe start to finish (except for the labneh&#8230;).  You never steer me wrong!!  Thank you.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-01-04T13:46:11-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-887278">
						<span class="date">January 4, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:46 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=887278#respond" data-commentid="887278" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-887278" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Penni" aria-label="Reply to Penni">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-887278 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-887653">
		<article id="div-comment-887653" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Julie									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Just took some old pitas out to make chips and of course this recipe pops up. Serendipity as always! A note to add re: pita chips. Instead of cutting before brushing I save time by splitting my pitas into halves, then I brush and salt each circle. Stack the circles up, cut them into wedges like a pie, then bake them. This also gives the advantage of adding a little oil to the back of the pita for extra crispness. Store in an airtight container.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-01-05T21:30:14-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-887653">
						<span class="date">January 5, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:30 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=887653#respond" data-commentid="887653" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-887653" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Julie" aria-label="Reply to Julie">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-887653 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-887960">
		<article id="div-comment-887960" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://@cakesandcrochetchic">Jess ~ Cakes and Crochet</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Made this for dinner tonight and it was a hit! The fella and the teenager even loved it &#8212; I was told to add it to the rotation. Really great blend of robust flavors on a warm and cool pallet! Thanks!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-01-07T18:41:13-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-887960">
						<span class="date">January 7, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">6:41 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=887960#respond" data-commentid="887960" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-887960" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jess ~ Cakes and Crochet" aria-label="Reply to Jess ~ Cakes and Crochet">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-887960 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-have-a-question" id="comment-888636">
		<article id="div-comment-888636" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Patricia Fogelman									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I&#8217;m wondering if this can be easily halved?</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-01-09T18:01:35-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-888636">
						<span class="date">January 9, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">6:01 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=888636#respond" data-commentid="888636" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-888636" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Patricia Fogelman" aria-label="Reply to Patricia Fogelman">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-888636 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 i-have-a-question" id="comment-890580">
		<article id="div-comment-890580" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://www.tangokat,com">Kathryn Wong</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>The finished photo looks great&#8230; what do you think of doubling the recipe, then serving the chickpeas and relish in the same serving bowl (for a crowd), with sauce and pita chips in the side? Is it good at room temp</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-01-17T11:56:23-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-890580">
						<span class="date">January 17, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:56 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=890580#respond" data-commentid="890580" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-890580" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kathryn Wong" aria-label="Reply to Kathryn Wong">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-890580 -->
	 </li>
	<ol class="children">
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-debsk bypostauthor even depth-2" id="comment-890697">
		<article id="div-comment-890697" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://smittenkitchen.com">deb</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I think so. It&#8217;s better warm-ish but mostly cooled off should be fine.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-01-17T23:39:38-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-890697">
						<span class="date">January 17, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:39 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=890697#respond" data-commentid="890697" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-890697" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to deb" aria-label="Reply to deb">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-890697 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-891018">
		<article id="div-comment-891018" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Sarah U									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Great recipe! I&#8217;ll definitely make it again. I think they&#8217;d be fun as an appetizer. I totally forgot to buy pita chips &#8211; because I have a knack for forgetting one very important ingredient at the store, almost every time &#8211; so I ate all the elements on a salad, which I still enjoyed. I&#8217;d much have preferred the pita crunch, though!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-01-19T17:53:33-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-891018">
						<span class="date">January 19, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">5:53 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=891018#respond" data-commentid="891018" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-891018" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Sarah U" aria-label="Reply to Sarah U">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-891018 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-898200">
		<article id="div-comment-898200" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Sonya									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made this last night with overnight soaked chickpeas, baked for a little over an hour.  Everyone, including 3 kids, loved it!  I&#8217;ve been using a lot of recipes from your cookbook and site lately and my 8 year old daughter said &#8220;Mom every night you cook incredible meals.&#8221;  Thank you, Deb!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-02-09T09:52:46-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-898200">
						<span class="date">February 9, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:52 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=898200#respond" data-commentid="898200" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-898200" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Sonya" aria-label="Reply to Sonya">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-898200 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-917436">
		<article id="div-comment-917436" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://blubyu1958.wordpress.com">blubyu1958</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>what a phenomenal dish!!! I absolutely loved every aspect, especially the yogurt, which I could&#8217;ve sinfully eaten it alone!!!!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-05-03T14:34:18-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-917436">
						<span class="date">May 3, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">2:34 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=917436#respond" data-commentid="917436" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-917436" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to blubyu1958" aria-label="Reply to blubyu1958">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-917436 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-923702">
		<article id="div-comment-923702" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Sarah									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made this today (soaked the beans overnight.  Loved it.  Since we are avoiding carbs, I put it over spring greens and made a big salad with all the fixin&#8217;s.  Really good!  Oh, and FYI, I mistakenly thought I had tahini, but Nope!  I just left it out&#8230;the yogurt dressing was delicious anyway!<br />
Also my dried beans took about 65 mins, but worth it!!!<br />
Thanks!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-05-30T21:36:42-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-923702">
						<span class="date">May 30, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:36 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=923702#respond" data-commentid="923702" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-923702" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Sarah" aria-label="Reply to Sarah">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-923702 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-have-a-question" id="comment-925206">
		<article id="div-comment-925206" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Lori									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Do you ever cook chickpeas in the slow cooker? I do it all the time with black beans, should work here too?</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-06-05T16:08:15-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-925206">
						<span class="date">June 5, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">4:08 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=925206#respond" data-commentid="925206" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-925206" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lori" aria-label="Reply to Lori">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-925206 -->
	 </li>
	<ol class="children">
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-debsk bypostauthor even depth-2" id="comment-925385">
		<article id="div-comment-925385" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://smittenkitchen.com">deb</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Yes and yes.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-06-06T11:08:05-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-925385">
						<span class="date">June 6, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:08 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=925385#respond" data-commentid="925385" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-925385" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to deb" aria-label="Reply to deb">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-925385 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-926464">
		<article id="div-comment-926464" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Yang Yang									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Soooo gooood!! Made this with canned chickpeas and they were creamy and succulent. Served it with the tomato-cucumber salad, homemade babaganosh and chips, and it could not have been a better summer meal! Already dreaming about the next time&#8230;nom nom nom 😋</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-06-11T20:27:04-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-926464">
						<span class="date">June 11, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:27 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=926464#respond" data-commentid="926464" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-926464" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Yang Yang" aria-label="Reply to Yang Yang">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-926464 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-928120">
		<article id="div-comment-928120" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://katecooksthebooks.com">Kate</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Made this last night as a snack for book group.  It was absolutely delicious but I would tweak the following next time: I used canned beans (after seeing the Cook&#8217;s Illustrated taste test where canned beat dry I may never use dry again) and I&#8217;m not sure you need the brief bake for them; maybe just a few more minutes stove top? Next, I will probably drain the beans if I&#8217;m serving as an app as the liquid almost immediately make the pita chips a soggy mess.  My relish was also a bit of a wet mess so I might drain the tomatoes and cukes a bit before combining and serving (and don&#8217;t make this ahead, as I did, it doesn&#8217;t hold well). Finally I thought the pine nuts were lost among all the other great flavors so I&#8217;d skip them.  The tahini-yogurt sauce, however, is luscious!  I can see what a great dinner this would be, when everyone&#8217;s got a knife and a fork and seated at the table but it&#8217;s a bit challenging as an appetizer as written.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-06-17T08:39:09-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-928120">
						<span class="date">June 17, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:39 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=928120#respond" data-commentid="928120" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-928120" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kate" aria-label="Reply to Kate">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-928120 -->
	 </li>
	<ol class="children">
	<li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id="comment-929232">
		<article id="div-comment-929232" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://katecooksthebooks.com">Kate Sheehan</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Also want to add: I had leftovers of this last night, four nights after I initially made it, and it was fabulous.  Drained the beans, plopped them on top of the yogurt sauce, threw some chopped grape tomatoes on top, drizzled with olive oil, S&amp;P, and the BF and I just scooped it up with pita chips.  So you can definitely do parts of this ahead!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-06-21T12:46:30-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-929232">
						<span class="date">June 21, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:46 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=929232#respond" data-commentid="929232" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-929232" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kate Sheehan" aria-label="Reply to Kate Sheehan">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-929232 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-961055">
		<article id="div-comment-961055" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Renie									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I love this dish! I prefer dried beans&#8217; flavor and texture here, but I&#8217;ve also made it with canned beans when I&#8217;m short on time and it&#8217;s still delicious. I usually cook the beans, bake the pitas, and toast the pine nuts a night or two ahead. The beans are so good on their own, though, I have never been able to resist eating them on their own straight from the pot and I have on occasion ended up with a less-than-optimal ratio of beans to fixings on the night I planned to serve the  actual meal&#8230;. Don&#8217;t skip any of the extras &#8211; I think they make the meal!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-09-08T08:40:07-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-961055">
						<span class="date">September 8, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:40 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=961055#respond" data-commentid="961055" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-961055" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Renie" aria-label="Reply to Renie">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-961055 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-971657">
		<article id="div-comment-971657" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Nina									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>These were amazing! I added some crumbled feta on top, of course. Thanks for a new favorite week night dinner!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2017-09-27T20:35:17-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-971657">
						<span class="date">September 27, 2017</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:35 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=971657#respond" data-commentid="971657" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-971657" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Nina" aria-label="Reply to Nina">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-971657 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-1004195">
		<article id="div-comment-1004195" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Kim									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>We use store bought pita chips for nachos sometimes&#8230;we call them pichos&#8230;this recipe looks delicious!  I think I could be a semi-permanent vegetarian&#8230;with the occasional chicken or hamburger.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2018-01-02T19:26:44-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1004195">
						<span class="date">January 2, 2018</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:26 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1004195#respond" data-commentid="1004195" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1004195" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kim" aria-label="Reply to Kim">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1004195 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1004317">
		<article id="div-comment-1004317" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Janet									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made this today after someone sent me a photo.<br />
I used some padron pepper with chickpeas and avocado with the tomato salsa cause I had one.<br />
Just a perfect meal. Yum.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2018-01-03T07:06:55-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1004317">
						<span class="date">January 3, 2018</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:06 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1004317#respond" data-commentid="1004317" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1004317" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Janet" aria-label="Reply to Janet">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1004317 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1004872">
		<article id="div-comment-1004872" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://whatatinyplace.wordpress.com">whatatinyplace</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>SO SO SO good!!! My whole family loved it.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2018-01-05T23:12:03-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1004872">
						<span class="date">January 5, 2018</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:12 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1004872#respond" data-commentid="1004872" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1004872" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to whatatinyplace" aria-label="Reply to whatatinyplace">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1004872 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1005506">
		<article id="div-comment-1005506" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Jill									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Made this tonight, and it was a hit—we&#8217;re even fighting over the leftovers for tomorrow&#8217;s lunch! My ten-year-old was sneaking chickpeas out of the pan while I was prepping everything else. </p>
<p>I used canned chickpeas, which were just fine. I think the brand of yogurt I bought was too tart, so I added extra tahini and a bit of honey to the sauce to mellow it out somewhat. And I deconstructed the cucumber relish, since my daughter isn&#8217;t a fan of raw tomatoes, so we could all add what we wanted. </p>
<p>And I took the suggestion in your note and included thinly-sliced radishes, which our local Lebanese place uses on their eggplant fatteh. Next time, maybe I&#8217;ll sauté or roast some eggplant and try to mimic their dish. That one uses smaller pita chips, which make it less of a nacho-style meal and more something you&#8217;d eat with a fork. So next time I may just cut the pitas into squares and toss them in a plastic bag with the olive oil, to save the time it took to brush all the triangles.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2018-01-09T00:04:48-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1005506">
						<span class="date">January 9, 2018</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:04 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1005506#respond" data-commentid="1005506" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1005506" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jill" aria-label="Reply to Jill">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1005506 -->
	 </li>
	<ol class="children">
	<li class="comment even depth-2" id="comment-1375067">
		<article id="div-comment-1375067" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Jill									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Made this again tonight, with the modifications I was considering above. I also added pomegranate seeds, and a drizzle of pomegranate molasses, which added a nice sweet/tangy note against the spicy chickpeas. They definitely added something to the dish! </p>
<p>The eggplant was good, but I think not really necessary, flavor-wise‚ since the chickpeas are really the star of the show here. I probably won&#8217;t bother next time, unless I have eggplants I need to use up. Or I&#8217;ll use the same technique for cooking the chickpeas, but keep the flavors more muted.</p>
<p>I did think the texture of the dried chickpeas were better than the canned, so I&#8217;ll try to stick with those in future. Also, I used heaping measures of the spices (except cayenne), which I think helped bump up the flavor a little. I also added a squeeze of lemon and some chopped parsley at the end, which really brightened up the flavors.</p>
<p>I soaked the beans for about 18 hours, and I did have some broth left in the pot. I&#8217;d made them a bit ahead of time, so I pulled them just before they were done, then simmered them uncovered on the stove to drive off the extra liquid while I prepped everything else right before we ate. Unfortunately, this did really consolidate the flavors, and made the chickpeas a lot spicier than I&#8217;d intended! Will remember to go easy on the cayenne next time, and add more heat at the table if needed. </p>
<p>Definitely a keeper, and I&#8217;m looking forward to experimenting with variations!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2019-03-07T08:59:12-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1375067">
						<span class="date">March 7, 2019</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:59 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1375067#respond" data-commentid="1375067" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1375067" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jill" aria-label="Reply to Jill">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1375067 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 i-have-a-question" id="comment-1007938">
		<article id="div-comment-1007938" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Sarah									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I love the chickpea portion of this recipe and just got an Instant Pot. Have you attempted this one with a pressure cooker? Thanks!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2018-01-17T18:27:28-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1007938">
						<span class="date">January 17, 2018</span>
						at						<span class="time">6:27 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1007938#respond" data-commentid="1007938" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1007938" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Sarah" aria-label="Reply to Sarah">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1007938 -->
	 </li>
	<ol class="children">
	<li class="comment even depth-2" id="comment-1076563">
		<article id="div-comment-1076563" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Joy									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Just made it tonight in the instant pot&#8211;soaked the chickpeas about 18 hours and then 10 minutes at high pressure with 15 minute natural pressure release (could have done more like 8-9 minutes&#8211;Rancho Gordo chickpeas, so they were fairly fresh as far as dried beans go). I think I could have reduced the liquid to three cups with the pressure cooker&#8211;I ended up with too much broth (and the spices concentrated in the broth) so I cooked it down separately and then poured the reduced and flavorful broth back over the chickpeas.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2018-06-16T19:08:40-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1076563">
						<span class="date">June 16, 2018</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:08 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1076563#respond" data-commentid="1076563" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1076563" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Joy" aria-label="Reply to Joy">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1076563 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1012058">
		<article id="div-comment-1012058" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Diane Barghouthy									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made these chickpeas (with canned chickpeas) last night. We had it with salad, your smoky eggplant dip and the yogurt flatbreads from the new book and everything was fantastic! I didn’t expect the chickpea treatment to make such a dramatic improvement upon the meager canned beginnings.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2018-02-01T13:20:46-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1012058">
						<span class="date">February 1, 2018</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:20 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1012058#respond" data-commentid="1012058" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1012058" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Diane Barghouthy" aria-label="Reply to Diane Barghouthy">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1012058 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-1037465">
