</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1037594">
		<article id="div-comment-1037594" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Carol									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This was totally delicious, and perfect for meatless monday.  Skipped the pine nuts, since my Monday evenings are insanely  busy.  Have you tried zataar as seasoning on your pita chips?  Heavenly!  Even just for snacking.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2018-03-12T17:04:07-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1037594">
						<span class="date">March 12, 2018</span>
						at						<span class="time">5:04 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1037594#respond" data-commentid="1037594" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1037594" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Carol" aria-label="Reply to Carol">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1037594 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1071035">
		<article id="div-comment-1071035" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Kim									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Might I suggest peperoncinis to take the place of the jalapeños on the nachos? And sliced kalamata olives are so good too. Love it!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2018-05-31T22:40:43-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1071035">
						<span class="date">May 31, 2018</span>
						at						<span class="time">10:40 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1071035#respond" data-commentid="1071035" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1071035" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kim" aria-label="Reply to Kim">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1071035 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1137282">
		<article id="div-comment-1137282" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Caitlin									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>We just had this last night and it is going into permanent rotation! So good, healthy, vegetarian, and really convenient for a work night, as I was able to make the beans and other components ahead of time. Even my kids (5 &amp; 2) loved it&#8211;the kindergartner had me pack leftovers for her lunch!  I also made Cook&#8217;s Illustrated&#8217;s homemade pita&#8217;s (soooo easy and amazing) and they went awesome with it! You rock, Deb!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2018-08-16T07:54:39-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1137282">
						<span class="date">August 16, 2018</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:54 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1137282#respond" data-commentid="1137282" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1137282" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Caitlin" aria-label="Reply to Caitlin">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1137282 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-1253784">
		<article id="div-comment-1253784" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="https://iprint.id/jasa-cetak-kain/">Jasa Cetak Kain</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Thank you now I can make it myself&#8230;</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
