	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-1298731">
		<article id="div-comment-1298731" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Rose									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I make this all the time.  The leftovers make the very best hummus ever.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2018-11-16T19:51:54-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1298731">
						<span class="date">November 16, 2018</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:51 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1298731#respond" data-commentid="1298731" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1298731" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Rose" aria-label="Reply to Rose">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1298731 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1360236">
		<article id="div-comment-1360236" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Rosie									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I decided to make this for dinner because I trust Smitten Kitchen and wanted something pretty hearty but healthy for dinner but to be honest I was not very excited about it. I should have been though! This was amazing. I used canned chickpeas (TJs). I don&#8217;t love cumin so instead of the 2 tsp of ground, I put a sprinkle of cumin seeds and upped the other spices a bit (used coriander, paprika, cayenne, and sumac). Had it with tomato/cucumber/red onion salad, yogurt with garlic/lemon/sumac, and the yogurt flatbreads from SK everyday. Such a good dinner and an awesome lunch of leftovers.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2019-01-28T13:51:50-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1360236">
						<span class="date">January 28, 2019</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:51 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1360236#respond" data-commentid="1360236" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1360236" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Rosie" aria-label="Reply to Rosie">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1360236 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1376839">
		<article id="div-comment-1376839" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Carie Lyn									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This recipe is on regular rotation in our house, regardless of the season. The flavors are way more than the sum of their parts, and every time I make it I can&#8217;t believe how delicious it is. I usually start with dried chickpeas and soak them. I&#8217;ve tried all 3 ways, though, and found that the canned chickpeas don&#8217;t absorb as much flavor, while the unsoaked dried chickpeas never soften up enough for me, despite lengthening the cooking time significantly. Still, I love that I have the option of throwing this together last-minute if don&#8217;t have the foresight to soak the beans. I usually halve the lemon-tahini yogurt topping, which is just enough for us. Thanks for an amazing recipe that the whole family loves!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2019-03-11T08:19:34-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1376839">
						<span class="date">March 11, 2019</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:19 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1376839#respond" data-commentid="1376839" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1376839" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Carie Lyn" aria-label="Reply to Carie Lyn">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1376839 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-1422787">
		<article id="div-comment-1422787" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Katie									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This is the only vegetarian dish that my meat-loving husband likes. We all love it in my family and eat this meal at least once a month.  I know this is an old post, but I just wanted to thank you for a wonderful recipe &#8211; one of our family favorites!</p>
<p>Also, I accidentally used smoked paprika once, and have made it that way since &#8211; it made an already fabulous recipe just a tiny bit yummier. </p>
<p>Thank you!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2019-07-02T23:47:59-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1422787">
						<span class="date">July 2, 2019</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:47 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1422787#respond" data-commentid="1422787" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1422787" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Katie" aria-label="Reply to Katie">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1422787 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this i-have-a-question" id="comment-1502749">
