	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1502819">
		<article id="div-comment-1502819" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Brian Hill									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Loved this so much. Our 8yo went back for seconds. She’s a sucker for anything “nacho”. Thanks for the great recipe&#8230;it will be made again in our house!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2020-01-01T18:21:55-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1502819">
						<span class="date">January 1, 2020</span>
						at						<span class="time">6:21 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1502819#respond" data-commentid="1502819" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1502819" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Brian Hill" aria-label="Reply to Brian Hill">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1502819 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1503668">
		<article id="div-comment-1503668" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Peggy Driehorst									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This was absolutely delicious!  My husband even ate the chickpeas (which he thinks he doesn&#8217;t like)  Loved the lemon tahini yoghurt.  I added some kalamata olives to the mix as well.  Will definitely make this again!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2020-01-03T17:50:10-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1503668">
						<span class="date">January 3, 2020</span>
						at						<span class="time">5:50 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1503668#respond" data-commentid="1503668" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1503668" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Peggy Driehorst" aria-label="Reply to Peggy Driehorst">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1503668 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1503912">
		<article id="div-comment-1503912" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Gail									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Unlike many SK recipes, this one served more than I expected. Delicious! In regular rotation.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2020-01-04T15:01:08-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1503912">
						<span class="date">January 4, 2020</span>
						at						<span class="time">3:01 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1503912#respond" data-commentid="1503912" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1503912" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Gail" aria-label="Reply to Gail">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1503912 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1505125">
		<article id="div-comment-1505125" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Julie									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I LOVED this &#8211; I used 50% more spices as I want to live dangerously, ha ha, I just like spicy food. My kids, to my utter delight, liked it and all the fixin’s, including the relish (I called it salsa to sell it) and declared it ‘better than good’. I agree, this is a keeper and will make it again and again. YUM YUM!! Thanks for sharing, Deb!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2020-01-08T05:23:42-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1505125">
						<span class="date">January 8, 2020</span>
						at						<span class="time">5:23 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1505125#respond" data-commentid="1505125" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1505125" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Julie" aria-label="Reply to Julie">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1505125 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1506800">
		<article id="div-comment-1506800" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Rebeca D.									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I just made this and it was absolutely one of the most delicious recipes anywhere!!!   I followed your instructions exactly &#8211; except that I used the Better Than Bouillon vegetable base.  I cannot say enough about how much my husband and I enjoyed this meal.  It was like a party &#8211; festive and delicious!  Thank you, Deb!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2020-01-14T20:54:31-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1506800">
						<span class="date">January 14, 2020</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:54 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1506800#respond" data-commentid="1506800" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1506800" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Rebeca D." aria-label="Reply to Rebeca D.">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1506800 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1506982">
		<article id="div-comment-1506982" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											clayton richard									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made this last night for the Queen and I &#8211; OUTA SIGHT!. I used a can of chick peas and reduced spices accordingly (1/2 tsp rather than 2 tsp). I had leftover (always extra in frig) small corn tortillas, which I cut into quarters and fried. Had ripe avocado, fresh cuc and tomatoes, red onion, scallions diced, grated pecorino, pickled radishes with salt and lime juice.</p>
<p>This will become a regular in our menu rotation.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2020-01-15T11:11:17-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1506982">
						<span class="date">January 15, 2020</span>
						at						<span class="time">11:11 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1506982#respond" data-commentid="1506982" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1506982" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to clayton richard" aria-label="Reply to clayton richard">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1506982 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1524369">
		<article id="div-comment-1524369" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Brooke Mantzke									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This was SOOOOO GOOD. And so easy!! A perfect meal in every way. Thanks Deb!!!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2020-03-05T20:50:04-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1524369">
						<span class="date">March 5, 2020</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:50 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1524369#respond" data-commentid="1524369" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1524369" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Brooke Mantzke" aria-label="Reply to Brooke Mantzke">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1524369 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-1558082">
		<article id="div-comment-1558082" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Katie									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I don’t normally post comments, but I just wanted to tell you that I’ve made this recipe four times in the last two months. It’s the only vegetarian dish that my carnivore husband will eat, my four year old loves it, and many of the ingredients are shelf stable or freeze well. (We haven’t been making the salsa but will once our garden gets going!)   Thank you &#8211; this is a family favorite for us even in ordinary times, and in these surreal days of social distancing and limited grocery options, it has been a lifesaver. </p>
<p>Just a thought, but I know I’d love a collection of Smitten kitchen recipes made largely with shelf-stable ingredients?  Or freezer-friendly recipes? Thank you so much!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2020-05-18T14:45:58-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1558082">
						<span class="date">May 18, 2020</span>
						at						<span class="time">2:45 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1558082#respond" data-commentid="1558082" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1558082" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Katie" aria-label="Reply to Katie">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1558082 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-1842063">
		<article id="div-comment-1842063" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											JANET GANNON									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I&#8217;ve made this several times now and I am obsessed.  Delicious.  I prefer canned chickpeas in the recipe and I put it back on the stove at the end to thicken the gravy.  This is a winner!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2021-01-05T20:54:19-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-1842063">
						<span class="date">January 5, 2021</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:54 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=1842063#respond" data-commentid="1842063" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-1842063" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to JANET GANNON" aria-label="Reply to JANET GANNON">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-1842063 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this i-have-a-question" id="comment-1912256">
		<article id="div-comment-1912256" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Stephanie									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Hey Deb! Is there a way to make this in the crockpot? I LOVE this recipe so much! Just curious what you thought! Thanks!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2021-02-07T17:11:48-05:00 class="comment-time">
