	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-2518369">
		<article id="div-comment-2518369" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://smittenkitchen.com">Patti Dyer</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This might be one of my favorite recipes this year. This made a lot of chickpeas so I’m going to use some of the leftovers to make hummus. It will be delicious! I added feta cheese to this and served it as a salad as well. The rest is going with me for lunch tomorrow. Thanks!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2022-02-27T18:52:24-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-2518369">
						<span class="date">February 27, 2022</span>
						at						<span class="time">6:52 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=2518369#respond" data-commentid="2518369" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-2518369" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Patti Dyer" aria-label="Reply to Patti Dyer">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-2518369 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 i-have-a-question" id="comment-2591324">
		<article id="div-comment-2591324" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Helen in CA									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Looking for a winter alternative to the tomato-relish, since tomatoes are out of season (and supermarket ones not worth eating).  </p>
<p>Thoughts?</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2023-01-02T19:35:24-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-2591324">
						<span class="date">January 2, 2023</span>
						at						<span class="time">7:35 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=2591324#respond" data-commentid="2591324" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-2591324" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Helen in CA" aria-label="Reply to Helen in CA">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-2591324 -->
	 </li>
	<ol class="children">
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-debsk bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-2591357">
		<article id="div-comment-2591357" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://smittenkitchen.com">deb</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Just do the cucumbers. Peppers might be nice too. I use grape or cherry tomatoes in the winter. Not amazing but will work here.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2023-01-03T14:25:55-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-2591357">
						<span class="date">January 3, 2023</span>
						at						<span class="time">2:25 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=2591357#respond" data-commentid="2591357" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-2591357" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to deb" aria-label="Reply to deb">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-2591357 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-2591444">
		<article id="div-comment-2591444" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Scott Nickerson									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I made this for dinner yesterday evening. It was really delicious. And there was a bit of the chickpea mixture left over which I have just fried up with an egg for breakfast. That was almost even better!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2023-01-04T13:42:09-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-2591444">
						<span class="date">January 4, 2023</span>
						at						<span class="time">1:42 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=2591444#respond" data-commentid="2591444" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-2591444" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Scott Nickerson" aria-label="Reply to Scott Nickerson">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-2591444 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 i-have-a-question" id="comment-2591684">
		<article id="div-comment-2591684" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Elizabeth									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Wondering if all of the liquid should be absorbed?<br />
I soaked the cp for 2 days, used 4 cups of broth and baked for 45 minutes. Still pretty soupy. Keep baking or is this much liquid normal?<br />
Thank you!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2023-01-09T11:03:44-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-2591684">
