	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-have-a-question" id="comment-2591858">
		<article id="div-comment-2591858" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Jacqui									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Would you recommend cooking my chickpeas in my instant pot to save time?</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2023-01-12T08:30:08-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-2591858">
						<span class="date">January 12, 2023</span>
						at						<span class="time">8:30 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=2591858#respond" data-commentid="2591858" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-2591858" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jacqui" aria-label="Reply to Jacqui">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-2591858 -->
	 </li>
	<ol class="children">
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-debsk bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-2591897">
		<article id="div-comment-2591897" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://smittenkitchen.com">deb</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Sure, you definitely could.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2023-01-12T16:36:16-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-2591897">
						<span class="date">January 12, 2023</span>
						at						<span class="time">4:36 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=2591897#respond" data-commentid="2591897" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-2591897" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to deb" aria-label="Reply to deb">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-2591897 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-2595680">
		<article id="div-comment-2595680" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Lisa									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This was an interesting supper—- yummy flavors, fun to eat, and very satisfying.<br />
I mashed the chickpeas a bit to make them more sticky and scoopable.   Roasted sweet peppers cooked in the oven alongside the chickpeas added nice color to the chickpeas.<br />
The cuke salad was tasty made with Campari tomatoes and tiny Persian cucumbers.  Also added a bit of fresh fennel because that was on hand.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2023-03-21T21:19:27-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-2595680">
						<span class="date">March 21, 2023</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:19 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=2595680#respond" data-commentid="2595680" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-2595680" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lisa" aria-label="Reply to Lisa">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-2595680 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-2607402">
		<article id="div-comment-2607402" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											<a href="http://theblueportugal.com">Jenny</a>
									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I prepared this recipe last night and it was an instant success. Even the leftovers are in high demand for tomorrow&#8217;s lunch! My ten-year-old couldn&#8217;t resist sneaking some chickpeas while I was getting everything ready.</p>
<p>I opted for canned chickpeas, which worked perfectly. The yogurt I used was a bit too tangy, so I balanced it with extra tahini and a touch of honey. I also customized the cucumber relish to cater to my daughter&#8217;s dislike for raw tomatoes.</p>
<p>I incorporated thinly-sliced radishes as suggested, a feature I&#8217;ve noticed at our local Lebanese restaurant. Next time, I might add some sautéed or roasted eggplant. I also plan to cut the pitas into squares for a less nacho-like dish and a more fork-friendly meal.</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2023-08-03T06:56:05-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-2607402">
						<span class="date">August 3, 2023</span>
						at						<span class="time">6:56 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=2607402#respond" data-commentid="2607402" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-2607402" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jenny" aria-label="Reply to Jenny">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-2607402 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-2632918">
		<article id="div-comment-2632918" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Rachel									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Oh my goodness, this was a hit! I was in a *big* hurry, so I made some modifications, while still staying true (hopefully) the recipe.  I dumped in some ras el hanout (Middle Eastern spice blend) in the chickpeas instead of the individual seasonings and then pressured them in the Instant Pot for 15 mins after an overnight soak.  Did not make my own pita chips but used Issa&#8217;s za&#8217;atar and thyme pita chips.  And didn&#8217;t have pine nuts, so we added feta on top, which really pulling things together. And, of course, a little hot sauce on top. (Also, for those that can&#8217;t go a meal without meat, I cooked up a pound of ground turkey with liberal salt, pepper, ras el hanout, extra paprika, and a dash of Worcestershire sauce.)  This will *have* to go into the regular rotation!!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2024-02-28T09:31:22-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-2632918">
						<span class="date">February 28, 2024</span>
						at						<span class="time">9:31 am</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=2632918#respond" data-commentid="2632918" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-2632918" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Rachel" aria-label="Reply to Rachel">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-2632918 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 i-made-this" id="comment-2677526">
		<article id="div-comment-2677526" class="comment-body">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<b class="fn author-name">
											Jan K									</b>
			</div><!-- .vcard -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>My husband, who tends to prefer meaty coups and stews declared it &#8216;fantastic&#8217; and &#8216;let&#8217;s make sure we save the recipe (&#8216;we&#8217; means me &#8211; LOL!).  I used Rancho Gordo dried chickpeas and soaked for about 20 hours. Oven cooking time was about 60 mins total and the beans were perfect.  Almond milk Greek yogurt to keep it dairy free).  Best part is that we have leftovers tonight!   Another great SK recipe &#8211; thanks Deb! YUMMMMMM!</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="comment-footer comment-metadata">
				<time 2025-01-19T12:52:38-05:00 class="comment-time">
					<a href=" https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/#comment-2677526">
						<span class="date">January 19, 2025</span>
						at						<span class="time">12:52 pm</span>
					</a>
				</time>

				<span class="edit-link">
									</span>

				<span class="reply-link">
					<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://smittenkitchen.com/2015/03/baked-chickpeas-with-pita-chips-and-yogurt/?replytocom=2677526#respond" data-commentid="2677526" data-postid="14933" data-belowelement="comment-2677526" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jan K" aria-label="Reply to Jan K">Reply</a>				</span><!-- .reply -->
			</footer><!-- .comment-footer -->

		</article><!-- #comment-2677526 -->
	 </li>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		</ol><!-- .comment-list -->

		
	
	
